title: heavenly chocolate honey dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl until well blended. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve with assorted fruits and chunks of angel food cake.

title: apple butter
directions: Make sauce of apples, add remaining ingredients and bake in oven for several hours until right consistency.

title: econo punch deluxe
directions: Chill ingredients.
Prepare ring 24 to 48 hours ahead.

title: broccoli and crab bisque
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion in shortening until soft.
Add broth, broccoli stems, 1/2 of potatoes, 1/2 carrots, celery, pepper, lemon juice, thyme, bay leaf, salt and pepper (cayenne). Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Puree veggies and broth in a blender.
Return puree to pot. Add remaining carrots and potatoes and cook soup over low heat, 5 to 10 minutes.
When potatoes and carrots are nearly soft, add broccoli flowerets.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add milk and crab meat and heat the soup.
Do not boil.
Serve bisque with croutons if desired.

title: spicy kidney's
directions: Drain beans and combine next 4 ingredients.
Add half of a tomato can of water.
Simmer on low heat.
Add more or less spice to taste.
I use these beans as a side dish or to liven up a taco salad.

title: muffins(almost as good as higbees)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line muffin pans with paper cups.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice until just before done.
Brown sausage (like you would ground beef).
Saute chopped onions and celery.
Mix meat, sauteed vegetables, onion soup mix and cooked rice.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add a small amount of water, about 1/3 cup. Cook in a 350° oven for approximately 20 minutes.

title: ester's round steak
directions: Saute the steak in skillet until brown.
Pour off drippings. Add the onion and cook over low heat for 40 minutes.
Mix the flour and brown gravy mix the the beef broth.
Mix into light paste and all at once pour this into meat mixture.
Add the mushrooms.
Cook for 15 minutes longer.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Makes about 6 to 8 servings.

title: kamba's pecan pie
directions: Set oven at 400°.
Cream together butter, sugar, vanilla and flour.
Mix well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in Kahlua, syrup, milk and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into pie pan.
In crust lightly press in some finely chopped pecans.
Then sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325°.
Bake until firm, about 40 minutes, then chill.

title: mexican quiche
directions: On floured pastry sheet, roll pastry to 12-inch circle; place in Ultra 21 (9-inch) quiche/pie pan.
Fold under extra pastry; flute edges.

title: del-mar-va barbecue sauce
directions: You will need a 1 1/2 to 2-pint container with lid.

title: make-believe lasagna
directions: Cook the pasta in lots of boiling water.
Drain; put in a bowl and toss with cheese and tomato sauce.
Add seasonings to taste. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Bake in a large pan. Mix pudding according to package.
Let cake cool and crush Heath balls.
Spread pudding over cake and sprinkle Heath bars over that layer.
Spread caramel sauce over that layer.
Top with Cool Whip and drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: nan's banana nut ice cream(5-quart freezer)
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add evaporated milk and half and half, stirring well.
Strain mixture into the ice cream cylinder.
Add mashed bananas and nuts.
Add enough milk to fill the cylinder.
Stir and freeze according to your freezer's instructions.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Over low heat, blend in a saucepan the tomato soup, gelatin, and cream cheese.
(Cream cheese should be room temperature and cut in small pieces.)
Stir these ingredients until they are well blended. Add the juice from the shrimp.
Remove from the heat and add the celery, onion, and shrimp. Add the mayonnaise and stir until well blended.
Pour mixture into a mold that has been sprayed with vegetable spray and refrigerate.
Serve along with your favorite snack crackers.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and slice potatoes, adding salt. Cook over medium heat until done.
Drain off water.
Mash the potatoes with electric mixer.
Cream.
Add the mayonnaise, milk and butter; mix again. Add sweet pickles, juice, onion, boiled eggs, pimento and dash of black pepper.
Mix together.
Refrigerate overnight. Ready to eat.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook and stir onion and bacon in 2-quart saucepan until onion is tender and bacon is crisp.
Add enough water to reserved clam liquid to measure 1 cup.
Stir clams, liquid, potato, salt and pepper into onion mixture.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until potato is tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in milk; heat through, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and condensed milk well; add whipped topping. Add all other ingredients.
Mix well and spoon into pie shells. Refrigerate for a few hours.

title: bagna cauda
directions: Melt butter in the casserole over low heat; add anchovies and sour cream.
Bring sauce to a simmer, stirring constantly.
Do not let boil.
Serve at once accompanied by cold vegetables and bread sticks.

title: carrot and whipped cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Grease well and flour three 9 x 1 1/2-inch round layer cake pans.
In large mixing bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat granulated sugar, salad oil and eggs until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Add carrot, mix well.
At low speed, gradually add flour mixture, beating just until well combined.
Batter will be thin.
Pour batter into prepared pan, dividing evenly.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Pour cream in bowl.
Add flour (add a little more flour, if needed).
Mix until it rolls into a ball.
Place on floured board and roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out and dip in melted butter.
Place on baking sheet and bake in a 400° oven until done, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: risi e bisi(rice & peas)
directions: In heavy 3 quart saucepan saute onion and parsley in 4 Tbsp. of butter for 5 minutes.
Add rice, saute, stirring occasionally, 5 min.
Add 2 cups water. bring to a boil, or until liquid is all absorbed.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients like a dough.
Take out 3/4 cup for crumb topping.
Mix in soda; add eggs and buttermilk.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Don't forget the topping on last.

title: herb-stuffed grilled chicken
directions: Preheat grill.
Soak wooden skewers or kitchen twine in a shallow dish.
Cut a pocket in thickest side of each chicken breast and set aside.
Melt butter in a medium skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; saute until tender, about 5 minutes. Add marjoram, parsley, thyme, salt and bread crumbs to skillet; mix well.
Spoon stuffing into chicken pockets; secure with wooden skewers or kitchen twine.
Combine melted butter and lemon peel in a small bowl. Grill chicken, basting frequently with the butter mixture, about 12 minutes per side.
Serves 4.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water, following package directions and drain.
Place macaroni in large bowl and add vegetables.
Add enough mayonnaise to blend salad and seasoning to taste.
Chill, then serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pork and rice
directions: Brown pork chops.
Spread rice over bottom of baking dish. Sprinkle all but 2 teaspoons of onion soup over rice.
Put mushrooms on rice.
Add water to liquid to make 3 cups.
Pour liquid on rice mixture.
Sprinkle chops with 2 teaspoons of onion soup mix.
Place chops on top of rice.
Cover tightly. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, pumpkin and vanilla.
Sift the next eight ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake cake in a 10-inch tube pan or Bundt
pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve plain or top slices with whipped cream.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until done.
Drain in colander and rinse with cold water.
Mix vegetables together well in a large bowl.
Add spaghetti; mix well.
Chill and serve very cold.

title: del monico nut cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream together shortening and margarine.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.

title: "anne's" d. b. s. candy
directions: Thoroughly mix sugar, coconut, pecans, vanilla, graham cracker crumbs and peanut butter.
Pour melted butter over the mixture; blend well.
Shape into little balls the size of a pecan.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips over boiling water.
Use toothpicks to dip balls in chocolate and place on waxed paper.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Drain.
Mix together beef, onion and soups.
In greased casserole dish, line bottom with Tater Tots.
Pour beef mixture over tots.
Use remaining tots to cover beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and browned.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Take sausage out of casing and fry, breaking up into small pieces.
Drain off fat and mix with remaining ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased pan for 12 minutes at 400°.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil together first 3 ingredients for 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper or buttered cookie sheet.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat the eggs with the milk.
Mix all together, except Velveeta cheese, in a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Top with Velveeta cheese; bake an additional 2 to 5 minutes, until melted.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Mix tomatoes and salt thoroughly.
Let stand overnight; drain. Combine with chopped onions, green and red peppers, sugar and vinegar.
Put spices loosely in a thin, white cloth.
Tie top tightly and add to tomato mixture.
Bring mixture to boil; boil gently with spices for 1 1/2 hours or until thickened, stirring frequently.
Remove spice bag.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal with sterilized caps.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: coke salad
directions: Boil Cokes. Add jello and stir.
Put in refrigerator to cool, not jell.
Add cream cheese (at room temperature), pineapple and pecans.
Pour in mold which has been sprayed with Pam.
Put in refrigerator to jell.
You may use other flavors of jello, if you desire.
This is a great holiday recipe!

title: creamy chocolate fudge
directions: Bring sugar, oleo and evaporated milk to a boil.
Once it boils, stir constantly for 8 minutes.
Take off heat and add peanut butter, marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Stir until thickened.
Spread in 9 x 12-inch pan.
For peanut butter fudge, add peanut butter chips instead of chocolate chips.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Combine ingredients and cook and place in 9-inch baked pie shell.

title: aaron's favorite banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add ingredients in order listed.
Bake in well greased and floured pan in moderate oven (325°).

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cut fruits in small pieces, pouring the lemon juice over bananas. Let stand 10 minutes. Then mix all the fruits together. Sweeten to taste and let stand 10 minutes more. Drain all the juice from the fruits and mix in mayonnaise, then fold in whipped cream. Pour mixture into refrigerator trays and freeze. Serve on crisp lettuce. Serves 6 to 8.

title: hacienda dinner
directions: Brown meat, green pepper and onions.
Add tomatoes, barbecue sauce and uncooked macaroni and cheese dinner.
Simmer 20 or 25 minutes until macaroni gets done.
Use large frying pan.

title: pasta primavera casserole
directions: Cook pasta as directed; drain.
Spoon into greased 14 x 10 x 2-inch baking dish.
Saute zucchini, red peppers, mushrooms and scallions in butter in large skillet for 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes; spoon over pasta.
Place flour in skillet; blend in milk.
Add broth, nutmeg and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Add spinach.
Pour mixture over vegetables. Cover; bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: standby casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Brown the ground beef in the butter. Pour off the grease and stir in the garlic, salt, pepper and tomato sauce. Cover; turn the burner to low and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Garnish with crumbled bacon before serving.

title: strawberry apples
directions: Cook apples; mash real fine.
Add 3 cups sugar and cook until thick.
Add jello and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Freeze in moistureproof container.

title: christmas rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour into 2 (8-inch or 9-inch) round pans (not with removable bottoms).
Bake as directed.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool.
Place the layer, top side up back into 2 clean pans.
Prick with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 cup water. Do the same with lime in another bowl.
Spoon the raspberry gelatin over 1 layer and the lime over other layer.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.
Dip 1 pan into warm water for 10 seconds and invert on plate.
Shake gently to loosen.
Remove the pan.
Spread layer with 1 cup Cool Whip.
Top with second layer (removed as the first).
Frost with remaining topping.
Refrigerate.

title: the atomic ahearn
directions: Cut loaf of bread lengthwise.
Spread one side of bread with mustard and the other side with garlic butter.
Add corned beef, ham, turkey and both cheeses.
Top with lettuce and onion.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop small amount on cookie sheet.
Mash down with a glass that is dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° until edges are brown.

title: bourbon sweet potatoes
directions: Bake sweet potatoes until tender.
Peel and beat with electric mixer.
Add butter, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and whiskey.
Mix well and place in a greased casserole.

title: pineapple crumb torte
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Crush vanilla wafers and spread one half of them on bottom of pan.
Cream sugar and butter until smooth and light colored.
Beat eggs well and add to batter. Spread over crumbs.
Fold well drained pineapple into previously whipped cream, then fold nuts into this mixture, sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Chill 12 or more hours in refrigerator, cut into squares when ready to serve.

title: one-pot spaghetti
directions: Cook beef and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender. Drain off fat.
Stir in broth, paste, oregano, garlic and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Add broken spaghetti, a little at a time, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Simmer gently, in covered pan, 15 to 17 minutes.
Serve with cheese.

title: lemon berry pie - diet
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Beat cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sweetener.
Stir in lemon peel and juice.
Add 1 1/2 cups whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Cover with strawberry halves.
Pour 2 cups milk in bowl, add pudding mixes and stir.
Let stand until thick.
Add 1 cup topping.
Spoon over strawberries.
Refrigerate. Garnish with topping and a strawberry.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: braised chinese vegetables
directions: Soak dried mushrooms and lily buds in enough water to cover for 30 minutes; squeeze and drain well.
Chop mushrooms; discard stems.
Cut lily buds into thirds.
Preheat wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add oil; stir-fry bok choy, pea pods, bean sprouts and water chestnuts in hot oil for 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms, lily buds, 1/2 cup water, soy sauce, bouillon granules and sugar.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Blend dry sherry into cornstarch.
Stir into vegetable mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: applesauce cake
directions: *Note:
Applesauce may be changed to blended fruit of any kind: figs, plums, peaches, prunes, bananas, etc.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pour rice in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine soups and broth and pour over rice.
Add mushrooms.
Place chicken pieces over rice mixture.
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: ranch beans
directions: Cut each bacon strip into 4 to 5 smaller pieces.
Saute bacon, hamburger and onions until meat is browned.
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Make sure to drain meat before mixing with other ingredients.
Bake until hot and bubbly, about 45 minutes, at 350°.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Place in ovenproof serving dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Garnish if desired. Serve hot with crackers.
Serves 25.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion
and garlic in oil.
Add beef bouillon or 3 beef bouillon cubes dissolved in 3 cups water, chicken broth, tomato juice, sauce, cumin, jalapeno, salt and Worcestershire. Bring to a
boil.
Cover
and simmer 30 minutes.
Add chicken and
diced tomato.
Cook 5 minutes.
Cut tortillas in strips; drop
into soup.
Serve
with
slices of avocado and shredded cheese sprinkled on individual bowls of soup.

title: barbecue on buns (sloppy joes)
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Simmer celery in water.
Combine beef, onions, celery and remaining ingredients in large skillet.
Simmer about 30 minutes or until desired thickness.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: city chicken
directions: Use wooden skewers; alternate pork with veal.
Dip into beaten eggs and bread crumbs.
Brown in frying pan.
Pour in drippings and bake in a covered pan in a 400° oven for about 50 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: In 9-inch pie plate, arrange broccoli; top with chicken. Combine soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese. Combine butter and bread crumbs; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Yields 4 servings.

title: panic
directions: Preheat oven to
Pour pie filling into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle
dry
cake
mix
over
filling.
Pour melted butter over cake mix and top with nuts.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fish chowder
directions: In a large pot add water and bring to boil; then add fish, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook fish until done about 10 minutes. Remove fish and debone. Add vegetables (except tomatoes) and Tonys Herb Spice to stock, cook until tender.
Add tomatoes, butter and fish bring to boil.
Then serve.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix ingredients all together one at a time.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for 50 minutes to an hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix butter, 10x sugar and 2 cups flour; stir with a wooden spoon.
Pat on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Combine eggs, sugar, 1/3 cup flour, lemon juice and baking powder in blender for 5 seconds.
Pour over partially baked crust. Bake 24 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Put a layer of potatoes, layer of onions and layer of hamburger in a buttered casserole dish.
Add another layer of each.
Heat soup and water; add salt.
Pour over mixture. Cook for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: country french chicken
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add chicken; saute 4 minutes.
Stir in water, soup mix and lemon. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken; discard lemon.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Cream
sugar
and margarine;
add 2 eggs and beat well. Add baking powder to flour.
Add flour and milk alternately to mixture;
add
1 teaspoon vanilla.	Pour batter in square pan, greased and
dusted
with
flour.
Bake
at
350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve
warm
with
strawberries, bananas, peaches or other berries can be used.

title: old fashioned lemon cheese cake
directions: Scald milk.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add enough hot milk to flour mixture to make a thin paste.
Stir paste into hot milk. Cook this combination over low heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture thickens slightly, for about 2 minutes.
(Do not cook longer or eggs will curdle.)
Cool this mixture quickly by placing it in the refrigerator.
(Do not allow mixture to cool at room temperature.)
Add vanilla and light cream to the cooled mixture. Pour into freezer can (hand-turned or electric).
Fill only to two-thirds full to allow for expansion.
Freeze and let ripen (recipe follows).
This recipe makes 1 gallon of ice cream.

title: fruited champagne punch
directions: Stir pineapple juice into concentrates.
Add 2 quarts water; mix well.
Chill.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush cookies.
Mix pudding mix and milk.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add pudding.
Pour over crumbs.
Reserve a few crumbs for on top.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken by bringing to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Drain well, chop chicken and set aside.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients and put into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish that is coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
First place exchanges (1 cup) equals 3 meat, 1 bread and 1/2 fat.

title: pineapple mint jelly
directions: In
large
saucepan, mix pineapple juice and water.
Add fruit pectin,
mixing
well.
Stir in a few drops yellow coloring. Bring
mixture
to a hard boil, stirring in sugar.
Bring to
a full
rolling
boil.
Remove
from heat.
Add flavoring. Skim off foam
with metal spoon.
Pour jelly into hot glasses. Cover at once with 1/8 in hot paraffin.
Add lids.

title: lemon cake filling
directions: Combine
ingredients
in the order given (flour, sugar, lemon juice, rind, water, egg, egg yolks and butter).
Cook in double boiler
10	minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool before spreading.

title: mama's vegetable soup
directions: Boil stew beef, celery and water for 1 1/2 hours.
Add other ingredients; cook until vegetables are tender.

title: quick and easy salad
directions: Sprinkle the pudding over the pineapple and fruit cocktail and stir thoroughly.
Let set a few hours before serving.
Just before serving, fresh fruits such as grapes and bananas may be added.

title: olive stuffed cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except olives.
Using approximately 1 teaspoon dough, wrap around olive.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
When frozen, store in plastic bag.
Take directly from freezer.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
(Three jars cheese will do, a 10 ounce jar of olives will do.)

title: best ever butterscotch pie
directions: Place brown sugar, cream and butter in a skillet or heavy pot and brown lightly. Mix together egg yolks, flour and milk; beat well. Add to sugar mixture; cook until thick, stirring constantly over medium heat. Add vanilla. Pour into baked crust. Top with meringue if desired.

title: mountain mama(a.k.a sex in the pan)
directions: Combine flour, oleo and pecans until crumbly.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: texas millionaire candy
directions: Melt 2 bags or 84 caramel candies with 3 tablespoons water in double boiler and add the nuts.
Drop on buttered, chilled cookie sheets and place in refrigerator.
Melt Hershey bars and paraffin. Dip caramel pieces and coat well.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Put half the cheese in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Combine chilies and eggs.
Pour over cheese. Top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven.
Let sit 5 to 10 minutes, then cut into 1-inch squares and serve with Doritos.

title: thickening for peas and corn
directions: Add a little cornstarch at a time until desired thickness is attained.
Shake well to mix.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 2 cups.
Store in refrigerator.

title: beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed.
Stir in browned beef, drained tomatoes and milk.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: bread sticks
directions: Cut buns lengthwise into 4 pieces.
Melt butter; add seasoning. Brush seasoning.
Mix on cut sides of buns.
Bake 1 hour at 300° until dry and crisp.
Yields 32 sticks.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Grease baking dish.
Add the fruit filling.
Sprinkle lightly with flour.
Add cake mix dry.
Pour butter over top.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread(2 loaves)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together sugar, oil, eggs, milk and vanilla; set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add to oil mixture.
Stir in poppy seed.
Bake in two greased and floured pans for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together everything but pecans until smooth.
Add pecans.
Pour into two deep dish or 3 regular pie crusts.
Bake at 350 degrees 50 minutes.
Lori loves pecan pie!

title: fresh tomato casserole
directions: Combine tomatoes, croutons, onion, salt and sugar.
Turn into buttered casserole.
Bake in 375°
oven from 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 5 to 6.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Dip chicken lightly in beaten egg. Then dip both sides in cheese. Then dip in bread crumbs until lightly coated. Season to taste.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Saute hamburger in 10-quart stockpot until brown. Remove meat and drain. Add oil to stockpot; saute veggies until semi-soft. Add browned meat to vegetables. Rinse beans and add to pot. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer until celery and carrots are tender, about 45 minutes. Makes 2 1/4 gallons of soup.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain and mash artichokes.
Blend artichokes with mayonnaise and lemon juice in blender.
Add cheese and garlic.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix all and pour into frozen pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center looks set.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon and drain.
Add onion and saute.
In kettle, put clams,
potatoes,
celery, carrots and seasoning.
Simmer until tender.
Dissolve
cornstarch
in
a little milk; add to clam mixture until thick.
Add
remaining milk.	Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened again.	Do not boil. Add bacon, onion and oleo.

title: best ever cabbage soup
directions: Combine ingredients.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: chicken and cabbage soup(makes 8 servings)
directions: Heat first 8 ingredients to boiling in Dutch oven; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Trim fat from chicken.
Cut each chicken breast half in half.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika. Heat margarine in a 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat until hot.
Cook chicken in margarine 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown on all sides.
Add chicken to soup.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: dessert
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar and flour until crumbly.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Mix Jell-O with 2 cups hot water and 1 cup cold water.
Set until syrupy.
Cream Philadelphia cream cheese with powdered sugar and cream.
Spread on cooled crust.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and then slice bananas over nuts.
Pour Jell-O over bananas and chill. Cut in squares.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: fancy franks
directions: Combine all ingredients in skillet and simmer for 15 minutes. Serve warm with toothpicks.

title: memphis slaw
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Whip with a wire whisk until sugar dissolves.
Combine cabbage and pickles.
Add dressing and toss gently.
Chill 1 hour.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and put into a Dutch oven and then add enough Tater Tots to cover the hamburger mixture. Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until Tater Tots are cooked.

title: multi-level marvel
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press into 8-inch square pan; chill.
Beat cream cheese with sugar and two tablespoons milk until smooth.
Spread over chilled crust. Arrange strawberries on cream cheese.

title: beef creamed - dried
directions: Place beef in hot skillet; sprinkle with flour. Add butter and stir until slightly browned; add milk and stir until thick. Serve on buttered toast.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, Crisco, eggs, potatoes and 4 cups flour.
Mix in enough of the remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead dough, either in the bowl or on a lightly floured board for 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and turn greased side up.
(Cover tightly and refrigerate up to 5 days if you're not ready to use it right away.)
When ready to use dough, punch it down and cut off amount needed.
(Whole recipe makes 48 rolls.)
Shape dough and allow to rise.
Heat oven to 400° and bake 15 to 25 minutes.
Brush with butter, if desired.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all the ingredients. Pour into large greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes. When cool, frost, cut into bars. Yields 44 bars.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together.
Add egg and beat.
Sift flour, salt, nutmeg and baking powder together.
Add these alternately with milk.
Roll and cut.
Fry in vegetable oil at 370°.
Makes about four dozen.

title: grape juice
directions: Fill quart jar with ingredients.
Add boiling water.
Process in canner for 10 minutes.
Tastes better if left on shelf for about a month before drinking.

title: easy rolls
directions: Melt margarine and add sour cream. Mix together with Bisquick. Spoon into greased muffin tins. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place raw bacon on bottom of casserole to cover.
Wash 1 1/2 cups of rice and drain.
Place rice over bacon evenly.
Mix 1 can of cream of chicken or cream of mushroom soup, garlic powder with 2 cans of water and pour over rice and bacon.
Place cut up chicken and mushrooms over all (season chicken to taste before). Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil and bake until chicken browns.

title: pie crust(old german recipe)
directions: In a small bowl, mix ice water, vinegar, egg and brown sugar. Keep in refrigerator.
In large bowl, sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add softened lard.
Work with fingers or blender.
If mixture seems wet or sticky, an additional half cup of flour can be added.
Make a well.
Add ice water mixture and blend lightly. Turn dough out on floured board.

title: vegetarian lentil soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour or until lentils and barley are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add more water, if too thick. Makes about 4 quarts.
Can be frozen.

title: irene kehler-smith potato salad
directions: Bake or boil potatoes; cool in jackets.
Peel cooled potatoes and chop.
Add all other ingredients and add to potatoes.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serves 50.

title: strawberry delight salad(diabetic)
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package directions; chill until slightly thickened.
Crush strawberries in blender or by hand; add to Jell-O mixture.
Add yogurt, vanilla and sugar substitute. Stir mixture until well blended.
Pour into 4 individual molds. Chill until set.
Unmold and serve on lettuce leaf.
Yields 4 servings.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Mix Philadelphia cream cheese, Roquefort and mayonnaise and stuff in the 3-inch sections of celery.
You may wish to further enhance the looks of these by sprinkling on some paprika, parsley or olive slices.

title: poppy seed southern chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Blend soup and sour cream.
Put over chicken.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be prepared in advance.

title: fresh vegetable casserole
directions: Cook carrots, onions and celery together until tender; cook broccoli 5 minutes. Drain vegetables when cooked and save juice for other use such as soup, etc. Combine cooked vegetables in large casserole. Heat can of soup slowly and combine with some of the drained juice. Pour this over vegetables. Heat in moderate oven. When thoroughly heated, top with grated cheese and a few bread crumbs until browned. Add salt if desired. Serve.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts. Be sure the mixture is well mixed together.
Press into balls the size of a walnut and roll in hand until about 2 inches long. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool completely and roll in powdered sugar.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: With electric mixer, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in chilies, taco sauce, chili powder, paprika, onion, garlic powder, taco seasoning and black olives.
Spread on flour tortillas.
Roll up tight as possible.
Refrigerate in storage bag approximately 4 hours or longer.
Slice in 1/2 to 1-inch pinwheels.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and baby food.
Add pineapple, raisins, oil, flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, vanilla and walnuts; mix well.
Pour into 2 round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar, salt, raisins and caraway seed.
Mix well. Combine buttermilk and soda.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Add water gradually while stirring to form a soft dough.
Spoon into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 50 minutes at 400°.

title: white texas sheet cake
directions: Beat Crisco, eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Add salt, soda and flour; mix, then add buttermilk, vanilla and almond.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in sheet cake pan.
Ice while hot.

title: how to preserve a husband
directions: Be careful in your selection; do not choose one too young. Take one who has been reared in a good moral atmosphere.
Some cooks keep theirs in hot water; others insist on keeping them in a pickle.
This ends to make them sour and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made tender and good when garnished with patience, sweetened with smiles and flavored with kisses.
Keep them warm with a steady fire of devotion.
When treated as directed, they will keep for years!

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add coconut, pecans and raisins. Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chitterlings
directions: Wash chitterlings thoroughly.
Remove excess fat and grit. Place in a large pot with vinegar and seasonings. Cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Place lid on pot and simmer 3 or 4 hours until tender.
Serve with spaghetti, cornbread and slaw.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: *Reserve 1 nicely shaped strawberry for top of pie.

title: frito casserole
directions: Cook ground chuck and chopped onion together until done.
Then add rest of ingredients and simmer.
Serve over Fritos and top with grated cheese.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown sausage in skillet; drain.
Break eggs into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Prick yolks; do not stir. Layer sausage and cheese over eggs.
Pour whipping cream over top. Bake for 45 minutes or until set.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook deep-dish pie shell and let cool.
Mix cream cheese with Pet milk.
Spread this over cooled pie shell.
Mix together 1 cup strawberries and 1 cup sugar in saucepan and let come to a boil. Mix cornstarch with a little water and pour into boiling mixture. Cook until thick.
Let completely cool!
Put 3 cups strawberries in blender and rinse.
Pour 1/4 cup sugar over these strawberries to sweeten.
Add drained whole strawberries to crust.
Pour cooked, cooled mixture over the whole strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in half and boil for 15 minutes in salted water. Rinse in ice cold water to halt the cooking. Slice. Line a baking dish with half of the bacon. Cover with cabbage. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and allspice. Add stock to cover the cabbage. Cover with bacon strips. Cover. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: waffles
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg yolks lightly; beat in milk and oil.
Add egg yolk mixture to flour mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into flour mixture, leaving a few fluffs of egg whites. Put 1/4 to 1/2 cup on hot waffle iron and cook until done.

title: she-crab soup
directions: Combine crab meat, half and half, lemon peel and butter and bring almost to a boil.

title: chocolate souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Coat bottom and sides of 2-cup souffle dish or two 10-ounce cups with butter (1 tablespoon of butter). Melt 2 tablespoons of butter and chocolate in saucepan.
Add flour and stir until smooth, stirring continuously. Gradually add milk until thick.
Add salt and remove from heat.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In bowl, sift dry ingredients.
In another bowl, mix zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Now you are going to mix all in one bowl:
beat eggs, sugar and oil until smooth.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Add zucchini.
Mix until well combined.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool pans 10 minutes before slicing.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Partially cook sausage, celery and onions.
Stir in rice, soup and water chestnuts.
Put into baking dish.
Add water.
Mix. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until rice is tender. Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: copper carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Drain and cool. Alternate layers of carrots, peppers and onions.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Do not dilute the soup.
Stir prepared mustard into soup before adding other ingredients or mustard may not mix well.

title: chocolate icing(cooked)
directions: Cook until it forms a ball in cold water, about 20 to 25 minutes. Stir the whole time while cooking.

title: spanish-style chicken and sausage
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet; add sausage and brown well, about 5 minutes.
Drain fat.
Add chicken, onion and green pepper and cook 5 minutes longer.

title: potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, chop 10 eggs.
Add potatoes.
In blender, mix milk, mustard, salt, pepper and onion.
Add mayonnaise and vinegar.
Blend until just blended.
Pour over potato-egg mixture. Mix well. Cover and chill.
When ready to serve, slice the remaining eggs and lay on top.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.

title: orange salad
directions: Sprinkle orange Jell-O on the cottage cheese. Let stand a few minutes, then stir in. Fold in Cool Whip. Then stir in pineapple and oranges. Let set in refrigerator 1 hour to thicken.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together except sugar.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Stir thoroughly and fold in dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Add pepper, onion and celery; saute in skillet with sausage.
Combine soup mix and boiling water in a large saucepan.
Stir in rice. Boil for seven minutes.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for one hour or longer.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Drain fruit. Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Blend in sour cream, sugar and salt. Fold in fruit, marshmallows and pecans. Freeze and cut in squares to serve.

title: mashed potatoes - make-ahead type
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Mash potatoes and mix in sour cream, softened cream cheese, 1 tablespoon butter, onion salt and pepper.
Gradually beat in enough milk to make potatoes fluffy and light.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with foil.
Chill up to 24 hours.
To serve, dot with remaining 1 tablespoon butter and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix the ingredients in a large bowl at low speed until moistened, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter in this and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 to 20 minutes.
Fill and frost with Coconut Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, milk and lemon juice. Mix well and pour into pie shell. Beat egg whites until firm. Add sugar and beat until fluffy. Pile lightly on pie filling. Bake at 325° until lightly browned, about 15 minutes.

title: chinese egg drop soup
directions: Bringer broth and ginger to a simmer, simmer for 20 minutes and remove ginger. Add soy sauce and salt to taste. Combine cornstarch and water, mix into smooth paste. Whisk paste into a the hot chicken broth. Simmer for 1 minute, until it sightly starts to thicken. Add onions and cilantro. Pour eggs from bowl in a steady stream into the simmering broth. Swirl the broth so it is moving in a circle as you pour in the beaten egg. Don't stir the broth for 45 seconds to 1 minute so the eggs have a chance to set. Lightly use whisk to break up eggs. Serve hot. Makes 6-8 servings.

title: onion soup chicken
directions: Salt, pepper and flour chicken. Brown in oil.
Remove.
In butter, saute onion, pepper and celery. Add lemon juice and brown sugar.
Mix all ingredients with the onion soup.
Pour over chicken and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Sprinkle with nutmeg and sugar.
Serve warm.
Garnish with lemons.

title: grayson chicken
directions: Line crock-pot with beef; place chicken on top of beef. Combine soups and sherry.
Pour over meat.
Cook on low 6 hours or high 3 hours.
May add water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: lima bean goulash
directions: Cook onion and oleo together.
Dump into baking dish along with all other ingredients, being sure to crumble up corned beef. Stir well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cukes; sprinkle on salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain. Add the remaining ingredients.
Let come to a boil.
Seal hot.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Mix all together. Crumble crackers on top.
Bake at 350° until solid.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Combine above ingredients and marinate for 3 to 4 hours. Grill for approximately 5 - 7 minutes, turning halfway through cooking time. Serve with "Stone Country Honey cup Mustard" cut with a small amount of white wine for dipping.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and butter; mix well.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let cool and cut into pieces.

title: beef roast
directions: Use a piece of Reynolds Wrap large enough to seal over the roast.
Place roast, adding salt and pepper to both sides, in the center of wrap.
Add Lipton and mushroom soup.
Seal Reynolds Wrap over roast.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour in casserole dish.
Spread crumbled Ritz crackers and pats of butter on top.
Heat in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: very good beef and romaine
directions: Slice partially frozen steak into 1/4-inch slices.
Combine water, cornstarch, sugar, lemon juice, soy sauce, salt and bouillon cube; stir well and set aside.

title: beef stew with biscuit topper
directions: Coat meat generously with a mixture of flour, mustard, paprika, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Brown meat well in hot shortening.
Dissolve bouillon in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Combine beef, bouillon and onion in a 2-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.
Stir in vegetables and parsley.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Remove from oven.
Increase oven temperature to 450°.
Place buttermilk biscuits, overlapping, around edge of dish, atop hot meat mixture.
Bake, uncovered, until biscuits are golden and vegetables are cooked.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: walnut danish roll
directions: Cream butter and 2 tablespoons sugar; add egg yolks and mix. Add flour.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk.
Add to mixture and mix well with hand.
Put in refrigerator covered.
(Let stand in refrigerator overnight.)
In morning, divide dough into two and shape into balls.
Meanwhile, beat egg whites stiff, adding 3/4 cup sugar to egg whites.
Chop walnut meats.* Roll out dough; spread with egg whites and sprinkle walnuts.
Roll up like jelly roll. Place on greased pan and let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: easy poppy seed bread
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes.
Turn batter into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: phadiaho(mexican spaghetti)
directions: Fry noodles in olive oil, stirring constantly until golden brown.
Add celery, onion, mushrooms, garlic, tomatoes, wine, water and raw ground beef.
Cook on medium heat until vegetables are tender and ground beef is cooked.
Then add cheese, 1 slice at a time, mixing well.
It's ready and it's good.

title: mama's chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken until tender and starts to fall off bone.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Remove the bones and gristle.
Cut meat into 1/2-inch cubes.
Mix with celery, eggs and pickles; add salt and pepper.
Mix mayonnaise and salad dressing together very well. Mix this into the first mixture.
If you want to add a touch to that, add 1/2 cup mellow apples (cut fine).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Work into this thoroughly two tablespoonfuls of lard, and wet with cold water.
Roll out thin, enough for one pie.
Pastry should be handled as little as possible, and placing it on ice or in a very cold place will make it flaky.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Combine blueberries, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Bring to a boil on low heat.
Add margarine.
Cook until thick.
Pour mixture into crust.
Let cool.
Chill until set.
Top with Cool Whip. Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into bite-size pieces, making sure to cut all fat off.
Tenderize, salt, pepper and flour meat.
Brown the meat and 1/2 of onion, chopped.
Drain off grease.
Combine soups and sour cream; add to mixture.
Mix chives and parsley flakes into mixture and heat slowly for an hour (or longer, if needed).
It can simmer several hours without hurting it.
Pour over rice or noodles. Serves 12.
Will freeze well.

title: frijoles
directions: Clean beans and rinse thoroughly.
Soak overnight in water or soak in hot water for 3 hours.
Put all ingredients in kettle and cover.
Cook over low heat until beans are tender, about 3 hours. Stir beans occasionally.
For thicker beans, cook with cover off the last half hour.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to package directions and allow to partially set.
Stir in other ingredients and allow to set until firm.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package. Arrange in the bottom of a casserole dish. Boil the chicken in salted water until cooked. Lay the chicken over the broccoli.

title: whatever burritos
directions: Mix ground meat, onion, garlic, salt and pepper in pot.
Brown well. Add taco sauce and simmer for 15 minutes. Spoon small amount of mixture onto center of tortilla. Follow by small amounts of red beans, tomatoes, green onions, sour cream and cheese.
Fold tortillas in 3 to form burrito.
These may be filled with vegetables, meat or whatever is leftover in the refrigerator.

title: cauliflower a la bienville
directions: Boil cauliflower until tender.
Drain.
Saute onion in butter. Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes on medium heat.
Add shrimp, salt and pepper to mushroom mixture.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add soup and cheese.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Mixture will be thick.
Stir while cooking.
Pour over cauliflower and sprinkle with parsley.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cream cheeses and add mayonnaise.
Fold in whipped cream and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Add 2 buttons garlic and let stand several hours.
Remove garlic and add salt and paprika.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter bottoms only of a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and set aside.
Beat butter, sugar, orange peel and vanilla in a large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add 2 1/4 cups flour and remaining dry ingredients.
Alternate with buttermilk to butter mixture, beating at low speed until just blended.
Toss rhubarb with remaining 1/4 cup flour.
Fold into batter with nuts.
Turn into prepared pan, spreading evenly.
Bake until wooden pick comes out clean, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix Wesson oil, sugar, celery and olives and pour over other ingredients. Marinate at least overnight. Longer it marinates, better it is.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Spread roll dough out on greased cookie sheet.
Press dough to fit pan.
Bake until light brown.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread on cooled baked dough.
Place vegetables on top of cream cheese mixture.
Add grated cheese last. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Combine soup and cream cheese in pot.
Heat until blended. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased mold. Chill 24 hours.
Unmold and serve with crackers or rye bread rounds.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend together oil and sugar.
Add all other ingredients. Bake in greased broiler pan at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: best rum cake ever
directions: Before you start, sample the rum to check for quality.
Good, isn't it?
Now go ahead.

title: oven fried pecan chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Dredge chicken pieces in pecan mixture and place chicken in melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken over.
Cover and bake an additional 30 minutes or until done.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt together with electric mixer.
Add milk, ginger ale and ice cream.
Serve.

title: irish coffee
directions: In chilled bowl, beat cream, confectioners sugar and vanilla until stiff.
Refrigerate.

title: mudd pie
directions: Put milk and instant pudding mix into Tupperware bowl or pitcher with lid. Shake until pudding is thick. Crumble cookies and layer bottom of pan with cookies.
Pour pudding over it. Top with Cool Whip. A small package of pudding and Cool Whip will serve 4 to 6 people. Great for camping; very little mess.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients, except cheese and bread crumbs.
Place in pan and top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix cake mix and dry yeast, then in separate bowl, combine water and salt.
Stir in dry mixture.
Gradually work in flour to make soft dough that can be handled.
Cover.
Set in warm place for 1 hour.
Punch down to shape into rolls.
Brush with oil or butter and place on greased sheet to rise for 2 hours.
Bake in 400° oven until golden brown.

title: escalloped potatoes(this recipe is good with any meat, but i usually serve it with
directions: In saucepan, boil potatoes until tender.
Cool, peel and dice. Place in a large mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients except eggs.
Mix well.
Dice 4 eggs and stir in mixture.
Slice remaining eggs and use to garnish top of dish.
Sprinkle dash of paprika on top.
Serves 10.

title: fried rice
directions: In 10-inch frypan, saute green pepper and onion in 1 tablespoon of soy sauce.
Add mushrooms and saute until they are hot.
Add Little Smokies and stir until heated thoroughly.
Add alternately the rice and a small amount of soy sauce.
Stir until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until slightly brown.
Remove bacon from skillet and fry the beaten egg in bacon fat.
Set aside.
Add cooked rice and fry for 5 minutes.
Mix thoroughly.
Add all other ingredients, cooked bacon and seasonings.
Garnish with scrambled eggs, ham and green onion.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together vegetables, cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.

title: chive potato and chicken casserole
directions: Prepare potatoes as directed on box and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook broccoli, drain and place on potatoes.
Boil chicken breasts.
Place on broccoli.
Mix the mushroom soup with the sour cream.
(You may use chicken broth to dilute the cream and soup mixture.)
Spread or pour the creamy soup over the chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake in oven 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peach shortcake
directions: Mix Bisquick and sugar, then add milk and eggs on medium speed until thoroughly blended.
Bake at 400° for approximately 13 to 15 minutes.
Cool and then slice into 2-inch squares.
Top with peaches and Cool Whip and serve.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Heat oil in a large frying pan and saute beef and onion until the meat changes color.
Add bread crumbs, tomato puree and sauce, garlic, salt, sugar, oregano and basil.
Simmer gently, covered, for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook the spaghetti according to directions on the package.
Drain and serve with meat sauce and top with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: no sugar added candied carrots
directions: Pour carrots with liquid from 1 can in medium saucepan. Sprinkle sweetener over and add butter.
Bring to a boil and cook over medium heat until all of the liquid is gone.
Stir occasionally. Add 1 tsp. butter when liquid is gone to glaze the carrots.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and mashed bananas.
Add flour, buttermilk and Pet milk alternately.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in well-greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Melt Velveeta cheese and pour into mixture.
Crumble tortilla chips slightly.

title: weight watchers pie
directions: Layer in bowl in order listed: graham crackers, banana, crushed pineapple, strawberries, vanilla pudding and Cool Whip. Chill about 1 hour.
Contains 270 calories.

title: honey-mustard chicken
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 inch pan; spread half the stuffing in the bottom, spread chicken mixture over the dressing.
Mix together 3 eggs and 2-1/2 c. milk; pour over the chicken.
Spread remaining stuffing over egg mixture.
Before baking spread 2 cans of cream of chicken soup over top.
Bake in preheated 350°F oven for 50 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Cream white and brown sugar together with oil.
Add eggs and mix.
Add flour mixture and beat.
Mixture will be thick.
Fold in apples and vanilla.
Nuts can be added if desired.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add eggs, crushed pineapple, oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Grease and flour bottom of loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: easy dirty rice
directions: *May substitute chicken or shrimp for ground meat and adjust seasonings.

title: lazy day casserole
directions: Line a 2-quart casserole with partially cooked ground beef. Place vegetables on top of beef, cover with undiluted soup, then top with potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: applesauce jello
directions: Mix red hots and Jell-O in water.
Add applesauce.
Put in Jell-O mold or dish and refrigerate.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars, eggs, oil and butter, then add cream of tartar, vanilla, salt and soda.
Then add flour.
Roll cookies in balls and then press down with fork on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: no peek chicken
directions: In large saucepan, combine the rice, onion soup mix, cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and milk.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pieces of chicken.
Cover pan tightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Do not peek!

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and oil.
Add salt, baking soda, cinnamon and flour.
Stir in (one at a time) carrots, nuts and pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: escarole soup
directions: Wash escarole and then boil 1 hour.
Strain escarole, then boil noodles until done and then strain.
Add noodles and escarole to chicken broth.
Cook on low heat until broth is hot.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Add spice, salt, soda and vanilla. Mix in apples, flour and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan 45 to 55 minutes at 350° or until well browned and top feels slightly crunchy.

title: old-fashioned vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat egg yolks in bowl until frothy.
Add sugar, whipping cream and evaporated milk.
Beat well until sugar is dissolved. Add vanilla, salt and half of the milk; mix well.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix all together the cake mix, eggs, sugar, sour cream and oil and pour 1/2 of batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Then mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture on top of cake batter and swirl in cake batter.
Put remaining batter on top of this and then add remaining brown sugar and cinnamon mixture. Swirl into batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Take out of oven after baked.
Punch holes in cake.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt; mix well.
Add all liquids and vanilla.
Freeze in hand turned or electric ice cream freezer.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Heat oil over medium heat.
Stir-fry pork for one minute.
Add pepper, onion and garlic; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
In bowl, stir pineapple juice with cornstarch, syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and catsup.
Add to wok and pineapple.
Stir constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil one minute.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: pumpkin-pecan bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add sugar; stir to mix thoroughly.
Make a well in the center of dry ingredients and add, all at once, the oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour batter into four 8 x 4-inch loaf pans, filling each half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until a wooden toothpick inserted in the center of the loaf comes out clean.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine soup, milk, thyme and pepper.
Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Unwrap dough from crescent roll can and place flat over chicken mixture. Bake an additional 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: california vegetable medley
directions: Cook
vegetables
according
to
directions on package. Drain and
set
in
dish.
Crumble crackers, put in a bowl and add stick of melted oleo; mix.
Cut cheese in cubed pieces and place over vegetables.
Pour
crackers
and
oleo mixture over vegetables and cheese.
Bake in
a 9 x 13-inch greased dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar-free banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put paper liners in muffin tins.
Beat egg whites, oil and milk, stir in bananas.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Stir in banana mixture until moistened. Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 23 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix and bake in 3 medium loaf pans at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Mix ground beef with mushroom soup.
Place in casserole dish.
Add Cheez Whiz on top and place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bell pepper and onion.
Season to taste with garlic salt, black pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Drain and combine with beans, sugar, mustard, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and barbecue sauce.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
In a Pyrex dish, put rice and 1 1/2 cups water.
Put brown chops on top of rice.
Mix together mushroom soup, 1/2 cup of water and package of onion soup mix. Stir and spread on chops and rice.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Take foil off and cook 10 more minutes.

title: onion barbecue chicken
directions: Cut up and skin chicken.
Cover the bottom of a 12-inch Dutch oven
with	half
of the sliced onions.
Add chicken and then equal
parts of
barbecue
sauce
and
soup
to cover the chicken. Place
remaining
onion on top of the chicken.
Cook for 1 hour with 12 coals on top and 12 coals on the bottom.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix in pan the sugar, cocoa, milk and butter and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.

title: cherry party salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: beer bread
directions: Grease one loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients and place in pan. Smooth the top by patting slightly.
Bake for 65 minutes at 375°. May be frozen when cooled.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Add all ingredients, one at a time and then mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in 2 loaf pans.

title: gracie's barbecue sauce for spare ribs
directions: Saute onions in oil until brown. Add and simmer the rest of ingredients for about 20 minutes. Place the ribs in a pan. Cover lightly with foil and bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Remove foil and spread sauce over all the ribs. Bake for 1 hour. Baste them frequently with pan drippings.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Combine figs, sugar and Jell-O. Let stand for about 25 minutes. Then bring to boiling point, stirring frequently, cooking for about 5 to 7 minutes. Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: easy chicken nuggets
directions: Slice chicken breasts into strips, then cut each strip into thirds.
Beat egg with a fork in a small bowl.
Add milk and mix. Drop pieces of chicken into egg-milk mixture.
Remove and roll in bread crumbs.
Place coated chicken into hot oil in a frying pan. Cook approximately 10 minutes on each side or until chicken is golden brown.
Drain on paper towel covered plates.

title: pineapple mandarin salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O using fruit and add water to make 4 cups.
Add fruit and marshmallows on top.
Chill.
At least 4 hours before serving, whip cream and fold in mayonnaise.
Spread on top of Jell-O and sprinkle with cheese.

title: baked pork chops and apples
directions: Melt butter in large skillet and add onion.
Saute until tender; remove onion and set aside.
Brown pork chops in butter and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Arrange chops in 13 x 9-inch baking dish and cover with apple slices.
Sprinkle with onions. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: holiday squash
directions: Cook squash; add butter, bouillon, onion and Cheddar cheese. Cook 10 minutes; then add eggs, bread crumbs and sour cream.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine catsup, tomato juice, salt, black pepper, red pepper, eggs, bread crumbs, onions and mustard. Blend well.
Add ground beef.
Mix gently, but thoroughly.
Line 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with foil; press in the beef mixture.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Spoon this mixture over top of batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done.
Will also make at least 3 dozen cupcakes.

title: great grandmama mcquown's strawberry ice cream cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Place frozen strawberries in hot jello.
Use 1 large tube pan.
Break cake in walnut size pieces. Place layer of cake in bottom of pan.
Add layer of ice cream, then several large spoonfuls of strawberry jello mixture. Alternate layers, ending with strawberry jello mixture.
Place in freezer.
Before serving, turn pan upside-down on plate until cake comes out.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Cream together well.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon two-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: french toast
directions: Layer Texas toast bread in 9 x 13 inch greased pan.
Cover bottom of pan and press to fit.
Beat 10 eggs.
Add milk, maple syrup and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Melt cream cheese in microwave and add sugar and
1/2 tsp. vanilla. Mix well and spread over bread.
Use all of mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown.
Let set 15 to 20 minutes before serving.
Serve with pancake syrup.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat together thoroughly.
Put in loaf pan.
Cover with 3 strips bacon (if you like that flavor).
Pour over meat loaf 1 (8 ounce) can tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef in onion and wine sauce
directions: Braise beef.
Add water, wine and soup mix.
Cover and slow cook for about 1 hour.
The liquid will thicken to make a sauce. Serve with noodles or white rice.

title: easy pizza
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together until smooth; add the cheese and pepperoni.
Mix well.
Spread on a pizza pan.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and oregano.
Bake at 350° until golden.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix butter, flour and powdered sugar together until like crumbs.
Pat into a 9 x 12-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sift the sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and baking powder together.
Add to eggs and lemon juice which have been mixed together.
Pour on top of baked crust.
Return to oven and bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: successful chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle uncooked rice in casserole. Top with chicken, soup, onion, salt and pepper. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: masar dal(serves 4)
directions: Pick and clean lentils and rinse in several changes of water. Place lentils, water and turmeric in 2 1/2-quart microwave-safe dish.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Rinse dried beef in hot water; drain and chop.
Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in milk and cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add dried beef and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 cups.

title: sugar cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put into greased 15 x 11-inch pan. Leave batter slightly lumpy.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on package, baking 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan.
Mix cream cheese, pudding and milk together.
Will become thick.
Spread on cooled cake.
Spread drained pineapple over pudding mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
This dessert may be frozen
in baking pan.
Transfer cut pieces to platter at serving time.
At Christmas, sprinkle with coconut tinted green and red.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together in punch bowl.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat together and pour in a 9 x 13-inch prepared pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit punch
directions: Chill juices.
Mix together.
Before serving, add the ginger ale.

title: crab-n-clam crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle evenly with topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until filling is thoroughly heated and topping is golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini with basil, pine nuts and parmesan sauce
directions: Combine the basil, 1/4 cup of the oil, the pine nuts, Parmesan cheese and garlic in a blender or processor fitted with metal blade.
Process, turning the machine on and off, until basil and nuts are coarsely chopped.
Set aside.

title: quick pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients well with fork.
Must be rolled between wax paper.
Makes 2 (one-crust) pies or one double crust.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Place hen, stew beef and loin roast in 4-gallon container with salted water and boil slowly, covered, until meat is very tender. Remove all meat from bone and grind, keeping chicken separate. Place ground beef and pork in broth. Add tomatoes, chopped onions, about 2 sticks butter, salt, red pepper, approximately 1 cup Worcestershire sauce and 2 cups catsup. This varies because of weight of meat. Cook until tomatoes disappear. Add chicken and corn and cook for 15 minutes more over low heat, stirring often.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in a covered saucepan in butter until tender.
Add beef broth, Worcestershire sauce, salt and dash of pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Sprinkle toast slices with cheese.
Place under broiler until golden brown.
Ladle soup into bowls and float toast on top.

title: lipton onion burgers
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients.
Shape into 8 patties.
Grill or broil until done.
Top with tomato and lettuce. Enjoy!

title: raisin honey drops
directions: Cream honey, sugar, butter, peanut butter and egg.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add rolled oats and raisins.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake on upper shelf of oven.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on racks.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: cheddar-garlic biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Stir baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Stir together butter and garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits.
Makes 9 biscuits.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Place oatmeal on a cookie sheet and bake until brown in a 300° oven.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken; save broth.
Cut chicken in bite-size bits.
Mix chicken, vegetables, soup and chicken broth.
Put in pie crust.
Top with other pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve.

title: stuffed canned biscuits
directions: Mix meat and cheese together.
Form little balls and wrap a biscuit around each one completely sealing each biscuit.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 375° until done.
Great for breakfast, too!

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Peel and cook the carrots; drain and set aside.
Combine soup, vinegar, oil, sugar, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard; cook for about 3 minutes.
Add chopped onion and pepper to hot mixture; cook 3 more minutes.
Pour over carrots.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: light bread
directions: Add yeast to 1/4 cup warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add shortening, salt and sugar to milk or warm water.
Add soft yeast and flour.
Beat well.
Place in greased bowl and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and let rise a second time if desired.
Work down and shape into rolls.
Place in greased pans.
Let rise and bake in hot oven.

title: avocado dip
directions: Blend all ingredients until creamy.
Cover.
Changes color when exposed to air.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: crazy for cranberries
directions: Turn leftover cranberry sauce into a sweet tangy barbecue sauce for chicken or turkey.
Simply combine 2 parts cranberry sauce with 1 part barbecue sauce and heat through.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature.
Mix rest of ingredients except olives.
Form into a ball and decorate with sliced olives.

title: sky-high stack-ups
directions: Combine
meat
and
onion
in fry pan.
Cook and drain. Stir in tomato sauce, chilies, chili powder and salt.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, place layer of 6 tortillas,
the
meat
mixture
and
cheese, and then 6 tortillas with the rest of the meat mixture and cheese.
Cover tightly with
foil.
Bake
at
for
minutes.
Cut in squares to serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
(Mexican lasagna.)

title: boneless breasts of chicken with white wine sauce
directions: Grease baking dish; put in chicken breasts and top with Swiss cheese.
Combine soup and wine; spoon over chicken.
Combine stuffing mix and margarine.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350 for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 persons (one breast each).

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill.
Have plenty of sliced fruit, apples, peaches, strawberries, etc.

title: jean's honey bars
directions: Mix in order listed.
Mix will be stiff.
Pat out in 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Do not overcook!

title: diet soup
directions: Add all ingredients in a large pot.
Cook only until vegetables are not quite done.
Pepper to taste.

title: mrs. shamitz's crumb cake
directions: Crumb flour, butter and sugar.
Take out 1/2 cup of crumbs for topping and add to this 1 teaspoon cinnamon; set aside.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla and sour cream to remainder of crumbs.
Mix by hand. Sprinkle top with crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes in an 8 or 9-inch square pan.

title: crunchy tuna salad
directions: Combine tuna, pickle, onion, mayonnaise and lemon juice and chill.
When ready to serve, add cabbage and toss together.
Add part of crushed potato chips and toss.
Heat in lettuce lined bowl.
Sprinkle remaining chips on top and garnish with tomato wedge.
Serves 6.

title: baked chicken with dried beef
directions: Grease bottom of casserole dish.
Lay dried beef on bottom. Put chicken pieces on top of beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour on top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: ooey gooey squares
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cream together the remaining 3 ingredients and pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Alternate each layer 1 cup bread crumbs, 1/2 can of asparagus tips, 1 sliced egg and 1 slice of cheese broken in small pieces. Repeat each layer.
Pour cream of chicken soup, to which milk has been added, over casserole.
Bake in oven at 425 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Peel and chop apples.
Pour 3 tablespoons sugar over apples, let set.
Sift flour, cinnamon, salt and baking powder; set aside. Mix sugar and oil, beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add orange juice and sifted flour mixture; mix well.
Add nuts and apples, stir by hand.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in oven at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Ice with canned milk, coconut and nuts.
Cook for 2 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream
margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour cream;
beat
with mixer.
Mix dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate
chips.
Bake
at 350° for 45 minutes.
No frosting.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook, drain and rinse spaghetti.
Add salad dressing and Salad Supreme seasoning to spaghetti.
Mix well, then chill.
Just before serving, add vegetables as desired.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour until it bubbles.

title: country cooking dish
directions: Cook meat, onion and peppers until done.
Add rice and seasonings, then add tomato paste.
Put into dish; top with cheese.
Put in oven and bake for about 20 minutes.

title: tiramisu
directions: Grate chocolate by hand or in a food processor.
Beat eggs with sugar by electric mixer in double boiler until tripled in volume, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Chill until cooled.
Beat Mascarpone until smooth and softened.
Blend egg mixture into cheese.
Dip flat side of ladyfingers into coffee/almond mixture and line bottom of a 9-inch glass dish.
Spread 1/2 of cheese mixture and top with half of grated chocolate.
Repeat cheese and chocolate layers ending with chocolate.
Chill covered at least 2 hours.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, eggs and cinnamon.
Line a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with wax paper.
Pour pumpkin mix in pan.
Pour dry cake mix over pumpkin mix.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool.
Spread with frosting mix.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple and dissolve jello.
Let this cool.
Add Cool Whip, nuts and cheese to pineapple-jello mixture.
Let "set" in refrigerator.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Mix 2 tablespoons cornstarch and 1/4 cup water.
Add to blueberries and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Cool. Add 2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining whipped topping when ready to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix chicken, celery soup, mayo and water chestnuts in casserole dish.
Melt margarine and mix with the dressing.
Pour on top of casserole.
Heat about 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl until well blended.
Store in airtight container.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons mix in mug and pour boiling water over.
Stir and enjoy.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough in pizza pan and bake in a 350° oven until brown.
Remove from oven and cool completely.

title: parmesan sauce for baked potato or broccoli
directions: Mix ingredients ahead of time so they will blend.
Serve on baked potato.
Also delicious on broccoli.
Can be stored in refrigerator for a long period of time for later use.

title: herb-grilled chicken
directions: Mix sauce. Brush on all sides of chicken. Place chicken on grill, skin side up, 6-inches from heat. Grill 45 minutes, turning and basting every 15 minutes.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain well.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Ready to use.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients except hot dogs.
Cut hot dogs into bite size pieces.
Pour sauce over hot dogs and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Brown slightly ground beef and onion.
Add chili powder, 3/4 teaspoon salt, Worcestershire sauce, canned tomatoes and red beans.

title: grandma bazuin's cocoa cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Cream together Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Alternate, adding dry ingredients and milk, until well blended.
Add the vanilla last.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes for cupcakes, 20 to 25 minutes for layers or 30 minutes for loaf cake.

title: tabasco beer
directions: If you are ever at a friend's house or at the bar and you want to gauge how much you have drank, do the following.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet saute onion, celery and broccoli in margarine for 3 minutes.
Stir in cheese, soup and milk, stirring until smooth.
Place rice in a greased baking dish. Pour cheese-vegetable mix over top of rice.
Do not mix or stir.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Sift together the first 3 ingredients.
Cream the butter or margarine and the brown sugar.
Blend in the eggs, vanilla and maple flavoring.
Add dry ingredients gradually; mix well.
If desired, chill for easier handling.
Shape dough into three 8-inch rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Place in freezer for at least 4 hours.
(Can be kept in freezer several months.)
Cut into 1/8-inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
