Press chopped pecans or walnuts into top of each cookie (4 or 5 pieces).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drizzle scant teaspoon Praline Frosting over each cookie.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: strawberry quench
directions: Blend flour, nuts, brown sugar and margarine well. Bake at 300° about 25 minutes. Stir 3 times; this makes your crumbs.

title: nana's banana bread
directions: Add all ingredients in listed order and mix well either by hand or with mixer.
If adding nuts, fold in last.
Pour batter in loaf pan and bake at 350° for one hour or until tester comes out clean.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Beat all ingredients on low speed 30 seconds.
Then beat 30 seconds on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions in oil and margarine.
Add beef and brown lightly.
Stir in tomato soup, mushrooms, peas, sugar and salt. Cover mixture; simmer 20 minutes.
Blend.
Stir in sour cream. Don't let sauce boil as sour cream may curdle.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: broiled t-bone steak
directions: Sprinkle steaks with salt and pepper.
Shake hot sauce on steaks.
Arrange onions over steaks.
Add water.
Cook in oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cook 15 minutes, then turn over and cook 15 minutes on other side.

title: mustard cheese dip
directions: Mix vinegar and mustard.
Let set 1 hour.
Add sugar and egg. Cook until thick.
Pour over large package of cream cheese and stir together.

title: green rice(broccoli)
directions: Mix well mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Add all other ingredients in order.
Place in casserole dish; cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a large pan, boil together the first 4 ingredients.
Remove from heat.
Add the baking soda; stir well (it foams up a lot). Pour over the popped corn in a large roasting pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes.
Remove and stir while cooling. Store in an airtight container.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Combine beans, onion, brown sugar, ketchup and barbecue sauce and place into a medium size baking dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Dish is done when a light brown coat forms on top of the beans.
Great dish to have at your next barbecue!

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until tender and drain.
In saucepan,
melt margarine; saute onion until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard, pepper and celery salt.
Add milk; cook until thickened. Place half of the carrots in a greased 3-quart casserole dish; add the cheese.
Then add second half of carrots.
Pour sauce over all.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal and pecans in large bowl; set aside.
In saucepan, heat the sugar, cocoa, milk, vanilla and oleo; let come to rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute and 15 seconds, no more!
Pour over oats and pecans; stir well.
Put by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown chops in hot grease.
Mix remaining 7 ingredients together and pour over chops.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 people.

title: lemon pie(recipe of mrs. r. o. moberly, a past president)
directions: Brown lightly in oven.

title: mother's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a rectangular pan. Beat eggs. Add sugar, cocoa, flour, salt, oil and vanilla.
Pour into pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ruby red rhubarb pudding
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 60 minutes.
(Jello and cake mix are dry.) This is best served cold when juices are thickened.
Add whipped topping if desired.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes and then add remainder of ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 2 to 3 hours until thickened.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken crunch casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Heat to boiling point.
Spread 2 cups crushed potato chips in bottom of greased casserole.
Pour in chicken mixture, cover with remaining potato chips. Sprinkle on cheese and dash of paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato and cheese soup
directions: Bring water to boil in a large saucepan.
Add potatoes and cook until tender; drain.
Reserve liquid, enough for 1 cup.
Add water, if necessary.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and milk.
Sift 1/2 flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to blended mixture.
Mix in blender until smooth, adding as much flour as needed.
Batter should be thin. Heat oil to 375° in an 8 or 9-inch iron skillet about 3/4-inch deep.
Pour about 1/4 cup batter into funnel.
Keep one finger over bottom of funnel until ready to drizzle batter into pan. Drizzle in circle motion in pan.
Let brown on one side, then the other.
Remove and cover with powdered sugar.

title: you name it!
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serve and enjoy!

title: halubki polish stuffed cabbage
directions: Core cabbage and place in enough water to cover.
With fork in one hand and knife in the other, keep cutting off the leaves as they become wilted.
Drain.
Trim the center vein of each leaf. Brown onion in butter or whatever is your best shortening.
Add meat, seasonings and rice.
Mix well.
Place in pot and cover 2/3 with water.
Arrange sauerkraut on top.
Add tomato juice.
Cover and cook slowly about 1 1/2 hours.

title: bran muffins
directions: Add boiling water to Bran Buds.
Set aside to cool.
Cream together remaining ingredients.
Add the cooled bran and water mixture; stir lightly.
This batter can be stored in a covered bowl in the refrigerator and bake as needed.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen muffins.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs with melted margarine; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Spread and press down.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 8 minutes; cool.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Jif, Crisco, light brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat just until blended. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with tines of fork.
Bake on baking sheet at a time of 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until set and just beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Place sheets of foil on countertop.
Remove cookies to foil to cool completely.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: watermelon whiz
directions: In a blender, liquify watermelon.
Add juices and honey.
Whiz briefly and pour into tall glasses.
Yield: Serves 6.

title: persimmon cake
directions: In the large bowl of an electric mixer, combine the sugar, vegetable oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift together the flour, salt and spices.
Combine the buttermilk and baking soda. Add the sifted ingredients to the first mixture alternately with the buttermilk.
Add the persimmon pulp and mix well.
Stir in the nuts.
Pour the batter into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 300° for 75 minutes.
Cool and frost with buttermilk frosting.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs plus vanilla.
Sift the flour, salt and cocoa 3 times.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Blend in food coloring. Dissolve soda in vinegar.
Fold in batter.
Bake in 3 layers in 350° oven.
Frost with purchased buttercream frosting.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the shortening or oleo, sugar and Egg Beaters.
Mix dry ingredients.
Mix bananas, water, vanilla and nuts.
Alternate dry ingredients and banana mixture with creamed ingredients.
Pour in greased loaf pans.
After loaves are cool, decorate with powdered sugar icing and candied fruit and nuts for holiday gifts.
Yields 2 small loaves.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: bernice heugatter's very good chocolate pie
directions: Cook all ingredients together until thick, then add margarine and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch baked crust.

title: dumplings(good ones like mom's)
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add broth and milk; mix well.
Turn onto a board.
Roll thin squares.
Add to boiling broth.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In large kettle, combine beef, water, salt, thyme, peppercorns and bay leaves.
Simmer 3 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove beef, peppercorns and bay leaves.
Separate meat from bones. Return meat to soup.
Add vegetable mix and canned tomatoes. Cover.
Simmer until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer noodles and sauerkraut.
Then cover with corned beef and onion.
Mix soup with mayonnaise and mustard and pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese then bread crumbs.
Slice margarine over casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and heat in small crock-pot.
May add about 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: elsie's sweet pickles
directions: Split or cut in rings all pickles. Soak in brine made of 1 pint salt to 1 gallon water for 3 days. Drain and soak in fresh water for 3 days, changing to fresh water each day.
Put in 1 gallon water, 1/2 cup vinegar and alum solution; simmer until hot through, 15 to 20 minutes; drain. Place pickles in jars. Boil vinegar and spices for 3 minutes.
Pour over pickles and seal. Will be ready to use in 10 days.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix 1/2 sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon together.
Mix together with biscuits in large bowl with lid.
Cover and shake well.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Mix together 1 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and melted butter. Drizzle over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small bite-size pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch dish or Tupperware.
Layer remainder of ingredients in order given.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread over the top as you would frosting.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 to 12 hours.
Cut out in squares.
Stays fresh longer since mayonnaise is not mixed into salad.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: Grate zucchini and onion and fry in butter slightly.
Combine with all other ingredients in round casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili dip
directions: Dump cans of chili and taco sauce into small saucepan.
Using medium heat, bring to a slow boil.
Chop cream cheese.
Add to sauce and stir until smooth.
Add chili powder to taste.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: baked apple slices
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Place slices into micro-safe dish.
Mix honey and orange juice and pour over apple slices. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Toss to coat well.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Recover and micro 2 more minutes.
Serve hot.
Yields 4 servings.
Has 55 calories, fat free.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Brown onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons of butter or oleo.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together.
Mix sour cream mixture with onion and green pepper.
Combine all with mixed vegetables.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in glass baking dish at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: zesty orange punch
directions: Stir some of the apple juice into the orange concentrate until the orange juice is melted and blended. Add the rest of the apple juice, soda and ice cubes. Cut some of the zest from the orange and lemon and add it to the punch. Slice the orange and lemon and float the slices on top of the punch. Makes about 35 six-ounce cups of punch.

title: spinach and pecan salad
directions: Toast pecans in butter in skillet.
Combine with spinach, mushrooms, water chestnuts, cucumber, eggs and bacon in salad bowl.
Add salad dressing; toss to mix well.
Let stand for 2 hours to improve flavor.
Yields 12 servings.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: In a covered blender container at low speed, blend all ingredients (except oil) until well mixed.
Then turn control to high speed.
Remove center of cover or cover; very slowly pour oil in a steady stream into the mixture.
Continue blending until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate dressing.

title: apple raisin spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for at least one hour.
Great on breakfast waffles or whole wheat bread toast.

title: seven cup salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: peasant soup
directions: Place beans in a Dutch oven and cover with water; bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from the heat; cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain and rinse; return to Dutch oven.
Add 6 cups water and all other ingredients except oil; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until the beans are tender.
Discard the bay leaves.
Add oil and heat through. Makes 12 servings.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook and stir zucchini, onion and margarine for 10 minutes. Add parsley flakes, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano.
Combine eggs and Mozzarella or Meunster.
Mix all together.
Take crescent rolls and press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan to form a crust.
Pour vegetable mixture over crust and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lollipops
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and water in a heavy saucepan. Cook, without stirring, until a candy thermometer shows a reading of 300°.

title: italian-seasoned chicken
directions: In a large strainer, rinse vegetables to thaw.
Place in 1 3/4-quart casserole dish.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Brush chicken on all sides with mayonnaise.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese.
Roll chicken in crumb mixture.
Arrange chicken pieces on top of vegetables.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika and remaining bread crumbs.
Cover and cook at 325° for 45 minutes to an hour or until chicken is tender.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: * I also have used 2 small cans of canned shrimp.

title: peanut divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in a 3-quart microwave-safe bowl; stir well.
Microwave mixture at High 5 to 6 minutes; stir well.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap; microwave at High 2 minutes.
Uncover; stir well.
Microwave at High, uncovered, 7 to 9 minutes, or until mixture reaches hard ball stage (260°).

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Sauce:
Mix green chilies, cream of chicken, chicken broth, chili powder, black pepper, garlic powder and onions together.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and cook over medium heat until soft ball stage.
Stir constantly.
Cool slightly.
Beat until mixture starts to thicken.
Drop candy rapidly from spoon onto greased wax paper to form patties.
If candy comes out too hard or too soft, place back in pan, add a little water and recook.

title: hot cake surprise
directions: Bake cake in oblong pan.
Ice cake with your favorite frosting while warm.
Layer scraps of frosted cake and ice cream in flute glasses or other stemware.
Top with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: potato and onion casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, onions, salt and cheese in a large greased baking dish.
Pour in chicken broth.
Add enough broth to fill dish halfway.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test for doneness of potatoes.

title: mary pelt dessert
directions: Crust:
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup flour over melted margarine.
Add 1/2 cup chopped pecans on top of flour.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes; watch.
Set aside to cool.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Combine soup, salad dressing and milk in a large mixing bowl. Mix in shrimp, water chestnuts, celery, parsley, onion, rice and Tabasco.
Add salt if desired.
Pour into casserole and cover with breadcrumbs which have been mixed with melted butter.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 plus servings.

title: hash brown breakfast quiche
directions: Press hash browns into bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate. Drizzle with butter. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes. Combine the ham, cheese and green pepper. Spoon over crust.

title: coconut mandarin layer
directions: Drain mandarins.
Arrange mandarin segments in bottom of serving bowl, sprinkle with sugar and coconut.
Repeat layers, ending with mandarins.
Chill for at least 1 hour before serving. This is especially attractive when put in a clear bowl.
This can be served as a side dish for curry or pork or as a dessert.
Serves 6.

title: mushroom salad
directions: Toss spinach, mushrooms, chopped eggs and crumbled bacon. Whisk remaining ingredients together.
Toss with vegetables to coat spinach.
Yield:
8 servings.
Carbohydrate 5 g, protein 6 g, fat 33 g, calories 333.

title: ambration cake
directions: Sprinkle pudding on pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on pudding. Keep refrigerated.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Pull out stems of mushrooms after washing.
Dry mushroom. Chop stems and mix with sausage.
Cook on low heat until red is gone from sausage.
Drain and mix with bread crumbs and cheese. Stuff into mushroom caps.
Cook 20 minutes at 350° or until brown. Mushrooms will turn dark during cooking.

title: peanut butter tandy kakes
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add flour, 1 teaspoon oil, baking soda and salt alternately with milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; while still hot, spread with peanut butter.
Cool in refrigerator. Melt Hershey bar in a double boiler with 1 teaspoon oil.
Spread over peanut butter and refrigerate.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Beat at low speed until light.
Gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy.
If necessary, add milk to make of spreading consistency.

title: focaccia(italian flat bread)
directions: Preheat ove to 450°.
For plain focaccia, roll out dough in a circle, as if for a thicker than usual pizza crust.
Brush with olive oil and bake on a cookie sheet or pizza stone that has been sprinkled with corn meal or flour.
Remove from oven in 15 to 20 minutes or when golden brown.
Serve hot with plain or flavored olive oil for dipping.
If desired, you may flavor the dough before baking by mixing in 1/2 cup chopped olives (Greek olives are great!), roasted peppers or whatever.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat egg; add sugar and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil.
Add orange extract and vanilla extract.
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip. Serve with fruit.
Store in refrigerator.

title: delicious hot crab dip
directions: Combine ingredients (except almonds), blend well by hand. Spoon into ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with toasted almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers or bread.

title: dig deep salad
directions: Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, fill half full with shredded lettuce. Layer onion, green pepper, peas, mayonnaise, sugar and cheese in order.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: In large kettle, cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain, reserving the liquid and setting vegetables aside.
In the same kettle, saute onion in butter until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Gently stir in reserved cooking liquid until soup is of desired consistency, approximately 1 cup plus or minus.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings (about 2 1/2 quarts).

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix stuffing mix with boiling water and oleo.
Cook, in another pan, the vegetables.
Boil until soft and drain.
Add chicken soup and sour cream; mix together.

title: spanish cream
directions: Soak gelatin in cold milk.
Dissolve in hot milk.
Pour over yolks.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Cook over low heat until slightly thickened.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour in mold and chill.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken in 4 cups water, salt and pepper.
Save broth. Cut up cooled chicken.
Place chicken in bottom of casserole.
Mix 1 1/2 cups broth with soup.
Pour over chicken.
Mix 1 1/2 cups broth with croutons.
Put on top of chicken.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza horns
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough.
On lightly floured surface, roll out each loaf into a circle, about 10-inches in diameter, about 1/4-inch in thickness.
Brush surface with oil.
With pizza cutter or sharp knife, cut each circle into 8 triangles or wedges.

title: herb chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In cup, mix thyme, rosemary, oil, paprika, salt and pepper.
With hands, rub chicken quarters with herb mixture.
Place chicken quarters, skin side up, on rack in large roasting pan.
Roast chicken 40 minutes (do not turn) or until juices run clear and it is golden.
Serve hot or refrigerate to serve cold later.

title: hearty beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef in large kettle, breaking it up with a spoon as it cooks.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring occasionally until soft.
Stir in beef bouillon, water, tomatoes, wine, herbs, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil; lower heat and simmer 30 minutes. Add rice and vegetables.
Simmer 20 minutes longer.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Freezes well.
This is thick soup; when reheated, add beef bouillon and water.

title: indian wedding cake
directions: Beat with a mixer until creamy.
Pour on cake as soon as it comes out of the oven.
Cool in the refrigerator for 5 minutes.

title: taco beans
directions: Brown beef and drain grease off.
Add pork and beans, mushrooms and taco mix.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put pecans in unbaked pastry shell. Mix other ingredients. Pour over nuts (pecans will float when coated). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot tea
directions: Simmer tea, cloves and cinnamon for 15 minutes.
Add orange juice, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Add 1/4 cup sugar to sweeten.

title: cherry-berry-delight
directions: Mash 4 large berries.
Reserve juice and discard berries.

title: shrimp sandwich spread
directions: Mix shrimp with cream cheese and add minced ingredients, using enough French dressing to make this to spreading consistency.

title: country baked french chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Combine all ingredients in a 9x13 inch baking dish; mix well. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix ingredients to your taste.

title: ham and swiss stuffed chicken breast
directions: Place ham and cheese slices on each breast half.
Roll up chicken from narrow end.
Secure with toothpicks.
In skillet in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on all sides. Spoon off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce to low, cover and simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Garnish with chopped, fresh parsley.
Serves 4.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole #2
directions: Cook broccoli. Chop and put in bottom of long baking dish. Cook chicken, debone and place on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; put on top of chicken.
Sprinkle curry powder on top. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs slightly and add to butter and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Sift flour and blend with creamed mixture.
Mix in pineapple including liquid.

title: port-glazed walnuts with stilton
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Spread nuts on parchment-lined baking sheet. Bake 8 minutes or until lightly browned. In saucepan, combine Port, sugar, pepper and bay leaf. Bring to a boil. Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened, 3 to 4 minutes. Discard bay leaf. Add walnuts to saucepan, stirring evenly to coat. Using a slotted spoon, drain nuts very well. Bake in a single layer on parchment-lined baking sheet. Bake 12 minutes or until nuts are mostly dry. Serve with Stilton and wafer crackers.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Dissolve sugar, molasses, water, butter and vinegar in saucepan.
Boil until it cracks in cold water.
Remove from heat; add soda and stir quickly.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Makes 4 to 6 quarts.

title: dump cake
directions: Place fruit in bottom of pan.
Add dry cake mix over fruit. Top with melted butter and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk. Bring to a boil. Add stick of butter and boil until soft-ball stage. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and peanut butter. Beat by hand until thick. Pour on plate to set.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until they boil up.
Remove from heat. Add baking soda, shortening, sugar, flour and spices.
May put in apples or other fruits.

title: baked pork chops and dressing
directions: Brown chops in skillet; place into a 2-quart casserole.
In small bowl combine bread cubes, onion and seasoning.
Add water and melted oleo.
Top each pork chop with 1/4 cup or more of dressing.
Combine soup and water in skillet used to brown chops and heat.
Pour over the chops and dressing.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turtle soup
directions: Combine turtle meat, beef stock, bay leaf, mace, lemon juice and Tabasco sauce. Bring to boiling and cook until turtle meat is tender.
Remove bay leaf and mace. Add egg white and season with salt and pepper. Add sherry after removing soup from heat.

title: our favorite crab
directions: Sauteing half the onion in margarine, gradually add the flour and half and half to make a thick white sauce.
Season with white wine and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Add hot sauce, salt and pepper.
Add 1 pound crab meat.
Fill shells, cover with bread crumbs and pour on melted margarine.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Cook for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Season with a dash of salt and pepper.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Wash berries and combine with 2 cups of sugar; boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining 2 cups of sugar. Return to heat and boil 10 minutes.
Pour mixture into open pan and let stand 2 days or longer, stirring often, before placing in jars. Preserves will be nice and thick.
Cook only 1 quart at a time, although you may add as many "runs" as you like to the pan to stand.

title: cheese straws
directions: Combine butter, cheese, flour, salt and cayenne pepper in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into pastry bag.
Press into straws on nonstick baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Yields 100 servings.

title: fried squirrel
directions: Dredge the squirrel pieces in a mixture of flour, salt and pepper (to taste).
Fry in oil at a medium temperature.
Turn the pieces often for even cooking.
Cook until browned and tender.

title: peanut patty
directions: Cook in heavy skillet sugar, milk, Karo and peanuts until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cool water.
Add vanilla and butter.
Beat until thick.
Pour out.
Patty will be soft.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken in a little white wine and seasonings.
Combine chicken, grapes and celery.
Whip together mayonnaise and sour cream.
Mix together about 4 hours before serving to allow flavors to blend.
When serving, garnish with almonds.
Preparation time: 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: pumpkin pie dessert squares
directions: Reserve 1 cup of the cake mix or topping.
In a bowl, combine the remaining cake mix, 1 stick melted margarine and 1 egg.
Press into the bottom of the pan.

title: mock potato salad
directions: Break cauliflower into florets in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with plastic wrap or glass lid.
Cook in microwave oven on Full power for 8 to 10 minutes or until cauliflower is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill for 2 to 5 hours before serving.

title: apple rings
directions: Warm in 9-inch square casserole dish until butter is melted.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine soda and buttermilk; let stand a few minutes.
Cream sugar, oleo and shortening.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour to creamed
mixture.
Stir in vanilla. Beat in pecans and coconut.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in batter.
Bake in three 9-inch pans, greased and floured, at 325° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together the ground meat, eggs, applesauce and bread crumbs.
Shape into balls.
Place into casserole dish.

title: twentieth century pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Sift flour once, then add baking powder and sift twice more, then add milk and flour, beating god after each addition.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix mixture and dip boiled wieners into it; drop into hot deep fat until brown. Serve with French fries and for an extra treat try some medium hot salsa ketchup.

title: lady finger cookies
directions: Melt butter; add other ingredients and mix well.
Mold dough into fingers and bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Roll in powdered sugar while still hot.
Do not use mixer; mix with hands.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: coconut pecan brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl combine brownie mix, water, oil and egg.
Beat 50 strokes by hand.
Add frosting and sour cream; mix well.
Spread batter in greased pan.
Sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.

title: grandma dodge meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon thoroughly and pack into a loaf pan.
Place 2 strips of bacon on the top and cover with 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute zucchini in 1 tablespoon oil until soft (not mushy), then set aside. Saute onions and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil until soft. Add next 5 ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Put zucchini in 9 x 13 pan and cover with tomato mixture; stir. Top with stuffing. Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Uncover. Top with Mozzarella and bake for 10 minutes.

title: quick caramel sauce
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over medium heat; add sugar and lemon juice, and cook, stirring constantly, 6 to 8 minutes or until mixture turns a deep caramel color.
Gradually add cream, and cook, stirring constantly, 1 to 2 minutes or until smooth. Remove from heat.

title: chop casserole
directions: Sear the chops on both sides in a hot skillet which has a cover.
Add all the remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly.
Cook very gently until the chops are tender, about 25 to 30 minutes. Serve with mashed potatoes or buttered noodles.
Serves 4.

title: parmesan chicken bake(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 1 1/4 hours.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Knead with warm water until dough is of rolling pin consistency.
Knead 30 times.
Roll into circles and cook on ungreased griddle.
Makes 10.

title: bean pot
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain and pour into slow cooker. Stir well.
Cook on slow 10 to 12 hours.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender.
Peel and cut into halves lengthwise.
Brown bacon lightly.
Add hot water to bacon and drippings.
Add potato halves.
Cover skillet and heat slowly until potatoes are thoroughly hot.
Remove potatoes to a hot dish. Add marmalade to liquid in skillet, heat to boiling and pour over sweet potatoes.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry compote
directions: Peel and slice the apples.
In a saucepan, combine the first 9 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered for 10 minutes or until cranberries pop and apples are tender. Drain and add the peaches and apricots; heat through.
Stir in pecans.
Serve warm or chilled.
Store in refrigerator.

title: icy cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F.
Fill muffin cups with paper baking liners.
Mix together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and mix.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, milk and vanilla and mix. Fill cups half full and bake until tops spring up.
Let cupcakes cool for a while.

title: pineapple dressing
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Fold in pineapple (juice and all) and bread.
Bake at 350° in greased, high sided pan or casserole dish (1 1/2-quart) for 1 hour.

title: carl's marinated shrimp
directions: Boil shrimp 3 minutes and peel.
Mix celery, pepper, onion, pimentos, oil, vinegar, cloves, water and brown sugar.
Mix thoroughly and pour over shrimp.
Mix well and marinate for 24 hours.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and green pepper in heavy pan. Add 2 cups hot water, milk, soup mix and salt and pepper to taste. Stir to mix. Scatter broken pasta over top. Cover and bring to boil. Boil 2 minutes, stirring twice. Stir in frozen peas and carrots; cover. Reduce heat and simmer 4 minutes or longer, until vegetables and pasta are tender. Add additional 1/4 cup water if needed.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples. Place in deep-dish crust. Mix sugar and flour together and sprinkle over apples. Cut margarine into pieces and place over apples. Pour 1/4 cup water over apples. Use thin pie crust for top crust of pie. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken tortellini casserole
directions: Cook tortellini; drain.
Roll chicken in flour and brown; set aside.
Cook onion in butter.
Add bouillon cubes, broth, sugar and mushrooms.
Bring to slow boil and cook 5 minutes.
In large bowl, combine tortellini, chicken, mushroom mixture and sour cream.
Toss gently.
Place in lightly greased baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: salami
directions: Knead well; place in refrigerator and knead once a day for 2 more days.
Roll into 3 or more rolls and bake on the fourth day for 2 hours at 200°.

title: cookies
directions: Bring the sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk to boil.
Add peanut butter, vanilla, salt and oatmeal.
Drop a tablespoon of mixture on wax paper and leave to harden (about 1 hour).

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Use a mixer to cream shortening in large bowl until soft.
Add sugar gradually, creaming until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Stir together applesauce, lemon peel and vinegar.
Add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in raisins. Pour in greased and floured 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: cherry pie
directions: Pour cherry filling in pan; pour cake mix on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
In a large bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into crust. Bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: beef roast
directions: *Can use regular rump; don't brown.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Mix together flour and seasonings and dredge the meat in mixture.
In a large casserole with tight-fitting lid, arrange in layers the meat and vegetables.
Add bouillon to hot water and then add Worcestershire sauce.
Pour evenly over casserole.
Dot the surface with butter.
Cover casserole and bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: roquefort cheese ball
directions: Blend the two cheeses together, using a fork.
Add remainder of the ingredients.
Put mixture on wax paper and form into a ball.
Put parsley on another piece of wax paper.
Place cheese roll on parsley and roll until covered.
Note:
The amount of Roquefort used depends on individual taste.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Bring 4 quarts water to boil.
Add spaghetti; cook and drain. Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Melt butter in a skillet.
Add carrots and garlic.
Cook until carrots are tender.
Add the carrot mixture to the spaghetti.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Mix well.
Press mixture into pie plate.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Add shredded cheese and bake for 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted.

title: refrigerator butter rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups of flour, yeast, salt and sugar.
Add milk and softened oleo; beat for 2 minutes with mixer on low setting.
Add egg and 1 cup flour.
Beat with mixture on medium setting for 1 minute or until well mixed.
Stir in remaining flour, small amounts at a time (I use a wooden spoon for stirring).
Mix well. Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Form into 40 bite-size meat balls, using a full teaspoon for each.
Brown meat balls lightly in oil.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Drain excess fat.
Combine chili sauce and jelly.
Pour over meat balls.
Heat, stir occasionally until jelly is melted.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes until sauce has thickened.
Baste occasionally.

title: hamburger rice pie
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, green pepper, seasonings and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Spread in greased 10-inch pie pan, forming a shell.

title: parmesan chicken breast
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan with no-stick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in margarine.
Coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time: 30 minutes.

title: hash brown pork bake
directions: In a bowl, combine sour cream and soup. Stir in hash browns, pork, cheese and onion. Transfer to a greased 3-quart baking dish. Toss cornflake crumbs and margarine. Sprinkle over top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes. Sprinkle with Mozzarella. Bake 10 minutes longer. Garnish with green pepper.

title: easy cheese lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Stir until moist.
Pat into pan.
Blend frosting mix into softened cream cheese; reserve one-half.
Add two eggs to remaining frosting mixture.
Beat for 3 to 5 minutes at high speed.
Spread over base.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost with reserved mixture.
Cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: pasta and carbonara sauce
directions: Beat eggs and cream until blended.
Cook pasta.
Put cooked pasta in a hot baking dish (250°).
Mix in butter and salami; pour egg mixture over and toss.
Add cheese and parsley.
Serve warm.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook
squash
and
onion
until tender, then drain real good. Mash.
Add salt, pepper, butter, cracker crumbs, sugar, 1/2
cup cheese, milk and egg.
Stir until blended.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients with lettuce on bottom in 13 x 9 dish.
Mix Miracle Whip with sugar and spread over top.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon over top.
Let sit in fridge overnight.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Mix together ground meat, onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic.
Brown in skillet, stirring often.
Prepare package of rice according to directions. When cooked, add can of black-eyed peas and tomatoes along with grated cheese.
Blend with the ground meat mixture.
Season to taste.
Put in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in conventional oven or 15 to 20 minutes in microwave.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Place bacon pieces in medium saucepan; place over medium heat. Fry bacon until crisp; add water and vinegar.
Heat to simmering.

title: squash fritters
directions: Note: You can omit cheese and use onions.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Mix all stuff together and pour over wings.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour (I marinate overnight).
Heat oven to 375°.
Drain wings and place on broiler pan.
Bake 30 minutes. Brush with sauce when desired.
Delicious on the grill.

title: hormel taco dip
directions: Microwave cream cheese until soft.
Mix together the cream cheese, chili and lemon juice.
Microwave until hot.
Serve with taco chips.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar and beat well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately with sugar and shortening mixture.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in three layers at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; add sugar and beat eggs.
Add chopped dates.
Cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Add nuts and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Pour this mixture over Rice Krispies and mix.
Set aside to cool just enough to handle. Roll into balls and roll into coconut.

title: pork chop surprise
directions: Brown chops in vegetable oil.
Sprinkle with salt and set aside.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream and seasoned salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 onions.
Spoon mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange pork chops over mixture and bake, covered, for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: walton's mountain coffee cake
directions: Generously grease a 10-inch, fluted tube pan.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan.
Arrange frozen dough balls on top of pecans. Sprinkle pudding mix over dough balls.

title: citrus slices
directions: Beat shortening and butter in large bowl until softened, about 30 seconds.
Add about 1/2 of the flour.
Add sugar, lemon or orange juice, vanilla, baking soda and salt.
Beat until thoroughly mixed, scraping sides of bowl.
Beat in lemon or orange peel and remaining flour.
Shape dough into two logs and wrap in plastic wrap or wax paper.
Chill 4 to 24 hours.
Roll logs in colored sugar.
Cut dough into 1/4-inch slices; cut each slice in half.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until edges are firm. Transfer to racks and cool.
Makes about 60 cookies.
Glaze with Citrus Glaze.

title: best scalloped corn ever!
directions: Beat together corn and eggs with a little salt and pepper. Layer in a greased casserole:
corn, a handful of uncooked noodles to cover the corn layer, sliced American cheese to cover the noodle layer.
Continue layering corn, noodles and cheese until the casserole is full.
End with corn.
This recipe can be expanded by using proportions of 1 can corn to 1 egg. Surprisingly enough, 4 people will probably consume three cans of corn!
This recipe is one I take to covered dish suppers and everyone asks for the recipe.
There's never any leftover.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes, about 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Beat egg and milk in bowl.
In another bowl, combine flour and corn meal.
Dip
tomatoes in mixture and flour.
Have shortening deep in skillet.
Cook until golden brown.
Salt to taste.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; stir well. Cover; refrigerate overnight. Serve immediately or store in airtight container in the refrigerator up to 2 weeks. Yield: 1 1/2 quarts.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta; rinse with cool water.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl and pour most of the dressing over the mixture.
Stir well and chill several hours.
Pour more dressing over salad.
Stir and serve.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Combine bread, sugar, butter and eggs with a spoon.
Add pineapple and milk; stir lightly.
Grease a baking dish; bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until crusty.

title: snack crackers
directions: Place the crackers in a large paper bag.
Heat oil until warm; mix with spices.
Pour over crackers and shake until well mixed. Let set for 1 hour.
Store in can.
Great snack.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift and mix first 7 ingredients.
Work in shortening and sugar.
Mix in vanilla, eggs and applesauce.
Bake at 350° in greased loaf pan for 70 to 75 minutes.

title: rhubarb-blueberry refrigerator jam
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients 15 minutes.
Add jello.
Put in jars and seal.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients together, then add the honey. Mix well.
Refrigerate until it starts to thicken.
Add the milk. Whip well.
Add the Jell-O.
Beat again.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with crushed vanilla wafers.
Add wafers on top also.
Let set at least 1 hour before serving.
Serves 10 or 12.

title: rich tea scones(makes 12 scones)
directions: Butter cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Cut in butter slices until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
In a small bowl, whisk egg until frothy; beat in milk.
Add milk and egg mixture to dry ingredients.
Mix until the dough gathers into a ball.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Divide into two loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: baked stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pan.
Cover with lid and bake for 8 hours at 250°.

title: mama harding's hot potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into fairly large pieces; place in saucepan.
Add enough water to just cover potatoes and bring to a boil.
Cut bacon into 2 to 4 pieces and place in skillet along with onion slices.
Fry together until crisp (almost burnt).
When potatoes are about half done, add chili powder, bacon mixture and a little of the bacon fat.
Cook until water thickens and potatoes are done, but not overdone.
Salt to taste.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine the flour, sugar, milk and almond extract; pour over butter.
Do not mix. Arrange peaches on top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bow tie pasta salad
directions: Combine tomatoes, scallions, garlic, parsley, basil, garlic powder and olive oil in a mixing bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 1/2 to 1 hour.
Toss in cooked bow ties.
Serve cold.

title: creole green beans
directions: Combine onion and green pepper in skillet with bacon drippings; saute until tender.
Blend together flour, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and mustard; stir into skillet. Add tomatoes and continue to stir until mixture thickens.
Add green beans and heat through; sprinkle with crumbled bacon.

title: chicken elegant
directions: In pan, brown mushrooms in butter. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil over low heat. Stir. Serve over patty shells. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and pull off bone.
Add chicken soup, mushroom soup, celery soup and sour cream.
Mix all together real well. Put in pan.
Mix stuffing with enough broth from chicken to moisten real good.
Spread over top of chicken mixture and bake in oven on 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until it gets hot and bubbles.

title: southern-style collards
directions: Check leaves of collards carefully.
Remove pulpy stems and discolored spots on leaves.
Wash leaves thoroughly.
Drain and chop.
Put greens in pot.
Boil until water turns dark green.
Then pour off and put clean water.
Then combine with smoked neckbone or ham hock.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, partially covered, 45 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add next 5 ingredients; mix well. Stir until bubbly, stirring frequently.
Pour into baking dish. Arrange biscuits on top.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter; mix with Pepperidge Farm herb bread crumbs. Debone chicken breasts; mix celery soup, 1 tablespoon minced onions, peas and 1/2 to 1 cup milk.
Layer bottom of casserole dish with crumb mixture.
Pour on chicken.
Bake 10 minutes.
Put remainder of mixture on top of chicken mixture and bake 10 additional minutes at 400°.

title: caramel pecan log
directions: Mix together thoroughly, marshmallow cream and sugar, using hands to form stiff dough.
Add almond extract.
Divide into 4 parts, making each in a roll about 5 inches long.
Wrap and freeze while making sauce.
In top of double boiler, add caramels, butter and cream.
Blend until smooth.
Place log in caramel sauce (working quickly) until coated with sauce, then roll in pecan halves to cover log.
Place on rack until set.
Wrap and store in covered container.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased baking dish.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Add to butter and onions; stir in vegetable and chopped eggs. Add 1 can (12 1/2 ounces) well drained, chopped tuna.
Stir in noodles and pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Add dash of Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate. Brown beef and onion. Drain. Stir in salt and pepper.

Spread in plate. Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs 10 seconds in blender or until smooth. Pour into plate. Bake 25 minutes. Top with tomatoes and cheese. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes. Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: green tomatoes parmesan
directions: Lightly sprinkle tomatoes with salt, drain on paper towels for 30-60 minutes. Meanwhile, combine cornmeal, parmesan, flour, garlic salt, oregano and pepper in a shallow plate. Dip each tomato slice into egg, then into cornmeal mixture. In a medium skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Fry tomatoes, a few at a time, for 2 minutes per side or until golden brown. Drain on paper towel-lined wire rack. Serve immediately. Yield: 4-6 servings.

title: old-fashioned brown sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs in small bowl and add sugar.
Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Add lemon flavoring.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
These are easy and sooo good!

title: holly's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients thoroughly in bowl.
Add flour and soda and mix well.
Blend in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°
or until lightly browned but semi-soft.

title: gingersnaps
directions: In large bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg, beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and chill. Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll each ball in sugar, place on cookie sheets 2-inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 1 minute, remove to rack to cool. Makes 48 cookies.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Clean mushrooms and slice.
Simmer, covered, 5 minutes with 1 tablespoon butter, onion and celery.
Add chicken broth to mushrooms; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.

title: pepper jelly(makes 6 jars)
directions: Blend peppers and vinegar.
Place in kettle with sugar. Bring to boil slowly.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Stir in pectin and food coloring.
Let
stand
minutes.
Skim off foam.
Pour into hot jars and seal with paraffin.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a large pan; add 1 cup brown sugar and spread evenly.
Lay fruit in brown sugar mixture.

title: millionaire pie 2
directions: Mix together cream cheese, oleo, 1 cup powdered sugar and beat until smooth and creamy.
Put into bottom of graham cracker crust. Divide carton of Cool Whip in half and reserve one portion.
With other portion mix pineapple, 1 cup powdered sugar and pecans. Layer on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with reserved portion of Cool Whip and sprinkle with pecan pieces.

title: low calorie party mix
directions: Melt oleo with Worcestershire sauce, onion and garlic powder. Stir until combined.
Add cereals and pretzels.
Stir together gently until cereals and pretzels are coated.
Bake in 250° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until crispy.
Divide into 4 equal servings of 145 calories each.

title: stuffed mushroom appetizers
directions: Wash and remove stems from mushrooms and chop finely.
Saute with onion in the butter until soft.
Stir in the bread crumbs or potatoes and the cheese.
Mix well.
Fill the mushroom caps with mixture.
Put on a baking sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Steam cut up squash and diced onion together until tender with salt and pepper.
Drain.
In baking pan, put squash and mash.
Add butter and more salt and pepper, if needed, to taste.
Add enough stuffing to soak up liquids.
Add 1 cup cheese and mix with squash.
Put the rest of the cheese on top as a topper.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: party punch
directions: Make syrup of sugar and 4 cups of water.
Boil until sugar is dissolved.
Add lemon jello and stir to dissolve.
Cool.
Add juices, extract and 1 gallon water.
Makes 100 servings.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt milk and caramels over low heat.
Add chopped pecans. Spoon out on a greased baking sheet.
Put in freezer for 1 hour. Melt 3/4 block wax and large bag chocolate chips.
Dip candy in chocolate.
Put back on wax paper until cool.

title: blackberry jam
directions: Put 2 cups sugar in saucepan, add enough water to moisten sugar.
Put berries in pan.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add 2 more cups sugar and boil 20 to 30 minutes.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: chippewa venison and wild rice stew
directions: Combine venison, water and onions and simmer, uncovered, for 3 hours, then add salt, pepper and wild rice.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Uncover and cook 20 minutes more until rice is tender.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Bring 1
gallon
of
milk to boiling point, stirring frequently. Remove from
heat
and
cool
quickly,
also stirring frequently.
When lukewarm, blend in
container
of
Dannon plain yogurt and 1 cup dry milk.
Pour into
gallon
or
quart jars
and
place in oven at lowest temperature.
Allow about
3 hours or until a knife inserted in yogurt separates it.
Cool completely and beat lightly with egg beater.
Serve with any desired flavor of fruit.

title: best ever cake
directions: Bake cake according to package instructions.
Let cool.
In saucepan, combine pineapple with juice and sugar.
Bring to boil and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Poke holes in cake with fork. Spread pineapple mixture over cake.
Prepare pudding, spreading to edge of cake.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with whipped topping and coconut.

title: aunt sharon's pumpkin nut loaf
directions: Beat shortening until light and fluffy.
Add sugar gradually. Beat in eggs.
Blend together flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Add pumpkin and vanilla; mix well until blended.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 4 ingredients.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and stir in.
Mix thoroughly. Press and mold into a long, smooth roll about 2 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper and chill until stiff.
Slice thin and place a little apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly browned in a 400° or moderate oven for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: margarita pie
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press into a lightly buttered 9-inch pie plate.
In a large bowl mix milk, lime juice and liquor (or orange juice).
Pour into a crust.
Freeze or chill.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks.
Stir in jam.
Mix flour with other dry ingredients.
Add flour mixture in about 3 parts alternately with sour cream.
Beat batter after each addition until well blended.
Bake cake in two greased 9-inch pans at 350° for 25 to 40 minutes.
When cool, ice with following.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put chunk style potatoes into a large bowl.
Add sour cream, mushroom soup, garlic powder, pepper and cheese.
Mix well and pour into a buttered dish.

title: rock cornish hens
directions: Mix together preserves, dressing and dry soup mix.
Spoon over hens.
Place on a foil-lined pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tender.
Hens may be cut in half and baked the same way, cut side down.

title: fruit shake
directions: Cube fruit and remove seeds.
Place all ingredients in blender and blend for 30 to 45 seconds or until smooth.

title: cheesy sausage muffins
directions: Crumble sausage and brown; drain.
Add soup and water.
Add biscuit mix until barely moistened.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen small muffins.

title: crab dip
directions: You will also need 1 jello mold.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Put cake mix and coconut in bowl, cut in margarine.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 10 minutes at 350°.
Arrange sliced peaches, drained, on top.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Mix sour cream with egg and spoon over peaches.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes longer at 350°.

title: hot herb bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread out 1 sheet of aluminum foil. Slice bread 1 inch thick each.
Spread a small amount of mixture (all ingredients except cheese) on each slice.
Arrange in exact loaf, coat top with excess mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Close foil.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°, then open foil for 5 minutes.

title: pizzaburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for cheese and spread on buns. Be sure to cover entire bun with mixture.
Place under broiler for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with strips of cheese. Return to broiler and broil until cheese is melted.
Yields 15.

title: savannah spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 3/4 cup syrup.
Heat together syrup, vinegar and spices; simmer 10 minutes.
Add peaches; cook an additional 5 minutes.
Remove peaches; strain liquid to remove spices.
Return peaches to liquid.
Serve warm, topped with whipped cream cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: quick 'n easy strawberry fluff pie
directions: Mix by hand thawed strawberries and whipped topping.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving. Serves 6.

title: lima beans and sausage
directions: Place lima beans in large pan and cover completely with water.
Cook for 1 hour over medium heat, stirring occasionally. If water evaporates, add enough to keep beans covered.
Add salt, diced sausage and Rotel tomatoes to beans and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Serve beans over white rice.

title: lemon rounds
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar; add egg, lemon juice and rind.
Combine flour with baking powder, salt and crushed candy.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix at high speed until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until edges just begin to brown.
Cool slightly.
Remove from baking sheets to cooling racks.
Frost, if desired.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble raw ground beef on bottom of Pyrex baking dish.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Pour soup on top of Tots.
Place grated cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together, then cut tomatoes in wedges. Arrange on top so servings include tomatoes.
Add taco chips last to keep them crisp.
Enjoy!
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving the juice. Bring all to room temperature. Whip all in a bowl, adding strawberry juice 1 teaspoon at a time. Chill. Serve on bagels or muffins.

title: sweet potato chiffon pie
directions: Combine gelatin, 1/4 c. brown sugar, salt, and spices in top of double boiler. Stir in beaten egg yolks, milk, water, and sweet potatoes; cook over boiling water 10 minutes. Refrigerate and stir occasionally until mixture is thick and syrupy. In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff; gradually add remaining 1/4 c. brown sugar and beat until stiff. Fold the egg white mixture into the sweet potato mixture; pour into a 9 inch baked pie shell. Refrigerate until set. Top with whipped cream and serve.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to package directions and chill. Combine onions, pepper, olives and artichokes together.
Mix mayonnaise, curry powder and liquid from 1 jar of artichoke hearts.
Mix everything well and chill before serving.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix.
Let sit a couple of hours.
Good with crackers.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Add butter.
Sprinkle salt and bread crumbs evenly over chicken.
Add 1/3 cup water for moistness.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 400° or until tender.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: mushroom rice casserole
directions: Lightly grease a 1 1/2-quart Pyrex dish.
Place uncooked rice in Pyrex dish.
Pour consomme and onion soup over rice.
Put mushrooms on top of this.
Place margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When it cooks 30 minutes, take out and stir, then cook last 30 minutes.
(Use dish with lid.)

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place chicken breasts skin side down.
With sharp knife, cut a shallow slit down center of each without cutting through to skin. Cut shallow pockets on either side of these slits.
Mix ham and cheese with garlic and a little white wine to moisten.
Season well.
Fill pockets in chicken breasts; seal slit with small finger-shaped fillet attached to each breast.
Put in refrigerator to chill 30 minutes.
Coat well in seasoned flour.
Brush carefully with egg, beaten with 1 teaspoon oil; roll in bread crumbs.
Heat oil; add butter.
When foaming, fry chicken breasts until tender, golden brown and crisp all over.
Drain on paper towel.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pudding cake
directions: Tear up one 10 ounce angel food cake into pieces in a 9 x 14-inch pan.
Pour pudding over this while pudding is thin. Spread fruit pie filling over this and let stand several hours. Then spread Cool Whip over and serve.
Freezes well.

title: beet salad
directions: Mix beets, beet juice, boiling water and lemon juice.
Add to cooled jello, the vinegar, sugar, onion juice, horseradish, celery, cabbage and eggs (optional).

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and cook over meats.

title: "luv-em" beans
directions: Cook hamburg, onions and bacon; drain.
Mix all ingredients in a large shallow pan (broiler pan or casserole).
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Take broth from chicken and mix with stuffing.
Cover bottom of casserole with chicken.
Mix soup together.
Do not dilute. Spread over chicken.
Put layer of stuffing over top of soup mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine carrots, sugar, butter, cheese and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; fold gently into carrot mixture.
Pour into greased ovenproof dish and bake for about 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Heat chicken stock to boiling.
In a small bowl, make a paste of cornstarch and 1/4 cup cold water or cold broth.
Slowly stir cornstarch mixture, sugar, salt and pepper into broth.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Add eggs, small amount at a time, while stirring to separate them into shreds. Remove from heat.
Add onions and stir.

title: onion and tomato salad
directions: Cut the tomatoes into 1/2 inch wedges, place in large serving bowl.
Slice onions into 1/4 inch wedges and place in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Place broccoli, cheese, onion and bacon in large bowl.
Set aside.
Mix mayonnaise, sweetener and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Refrigerate one hour before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, onion, green pepper, toast, egg, 1/2 cup tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Mold.
Combine 1/2 cup tomato sauce, sugar, vinegar and dry mustard.
Pour over meat.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Add sugar. Add beaten egg and cooled melted margarine.
Stir in half of the flour and beat well.
Add remaining flour and beat.
Place in airtight bowl and keep in refrigerator until needed.
The dough will keep for several days in the refrigerator.

title: irish bread #1
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients and then add remainder of ingredients.
Mix all together in a large bowl, then turn out onto a floured board and knead lightly for a few turns.
Shape into a round loaf.
Place the loaf into a greased and lightly floured 9 or 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: linguini
directions: Mix all ingredients well and cover.
Refrigerate overnight. Mix well before serving.

title: chicken with chipped beef
directions: Line bottom of a greased casserole with chipped beef. Wrap each breast with slice of bacon and place on chipped beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Refrigerate until ready to
cook.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 hours at 275°. Serves 6 to 8.
Great easy company dish.

title: raisin pie
directions: In a saucepan, stir together sugar and flour.
Add water and mix well.
Stir in raisins, salt and cinnamon.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat;
stir in butter.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: oven-fried pecan chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put the biscuit mix, salt, paprika, poultry seasoning and pecans in a bowl and mix.
Pour evaporated milk in a separate bowl.
Dip the chicken pieces in the milk, then the biscuit mixture.
Coat pieces thoroughly.
Place pieces in the pan, skin side down.
Do not let pieces touch.
Pour melted butter over the chicken.
Bake for 1 hour, or until tender.

title: banana split torte
directions: Mix crushed vanilla wafers and 1 stick of butter.
Pat into large cake pan.

title: peanut butter crunch cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°; grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, brown sugar and peanut butter.
Beat at low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 cup of peanut butter mixture.
To remaining peanut butter mixture, add water, oil and eggs.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Stir 1/4 cup of peanut chips and 1/4 cup chocolate chips into batter.
Pour batter into pan.
In small bowl, combine reserved peanut butter mixture, remaining chocolate chips and peanuts.
Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Sprinkle, at once, remaining peanut butter chips. Gently press into top of cake.

title: chicken marbella
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine chicken quarters, garlic, oregano, pepper, salt, vinegar, olive oil, prunes, olives, capers and juice and bay leaves.
Arrange chicken in a single layer in 2 large shallow baking pans and spoon marinade over evenly.
Sprinkle chickens with brown sugar and pour white wine around them.
Bake for 50 minutes to 1 hour, basting frequently with pan juices.
With slotted spoon, transfer chicken, prunes, olives and capers to platter.
Sprinkle with parsley or cilantro.

title: raspberry muffins
directions: Mix all together and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: creamy egg nog pie
directions: In medium saucepan combine pudding mix, 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg and egg nog. Mix well over medium heat.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rum, if desired. Cool or chill thoroughly.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into prepared pastry shell. Garnish with additional nutmeg.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: nana's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl, blend together all ingredients.
Turn into shell and bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, heat 3 tablespoons of butter; saute onion until tender.
Add 2 cups bread crumbs, sugar, salt, pepper and cayenne.
Arrange layers of tomatoes in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with layer of onion-bread mixture. Continue until all is used, ending with tomatoes on top.
Combine 1/4 cup bread crumbs with 1 tablespoon butter; sprinkle over tomatoes.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: bob andy pie
directions: Mix first
ingredients; add melted margarine and egg yolks and
whites.
Add
milk.
Pour
into
unbaked pie crust; bake in a 400° oven.
Take out while filling is still soft.

title: pecan pie(club member: clint hudson)
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and flour. Beat and add vanilla. Add Karo syrup and beat. Add pecans and beat. Pour into pie shell. Bake about 3 hours real slow.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Mix together all ingredients and put over pork or beef roast, chopped.
Simmer.

title: corn and rice salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine corn, rice, pepper, onion and olives. In a screw-top jar, combine oil, vinegar, soy sauce, parsley, mustard and garlic powder.
Shake to mix; pour over corn mixture. Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
To serve, stir in tomatoes.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: impossible zucchini tomato pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch quiche dish or pie plate.
Sprinkle zucchini, tomatoes, onion and cheese in plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted into center comes out clean, approximately 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook tomatoes and onions together.
Strain and cool.
Make paste of flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add slowly to tomato and onion mixture.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes.
Put in jar; seal.
Process in water bath for 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown celery and onion in 1 tablespoon margarine; beat soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Combine above ingredients and add rice and mushrooms.
Pour into long casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cube venison casserole
directions: Place venison in large Pyrex dish.
Layer onion, carrots and potatoes on top.
Heat soup with margarine and pour over casserole. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: irish soda bread #1
directions: In a bowl, stir together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add the raisins, the caraway seed and enough buttermilk to hold all ingredients together.
Don't make too wet.

title: treasure cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a small bowl.
Beat brown sugar, butter, Crisco, sugar and vanilla until combined.
Add egg; beat until creamy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Gently stir in Treasures and nuts.
Drop by heaping tablespoon 2-inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 9 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on cookie sheets 2 minutes and then remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen large cookies.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain mixed veggies and whole corn or favorite veggie and mix together.
Add enough mayo to wet veggies (about 3/4 cup).
Next, add Cheddar cheese.
Mix well.
Top with fried onions, crushed potato chips or cracker crumbs.
Just take your pick.
Add a little extra cheese on top and heat in oven until cheese melts (about 5 minutes at 350°).
Great and easy!

title: new england squares
directions: Blend graham cracker crumbs, mincemeat and sweetened condensed milk.
Turn into well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned (about 30 minutes).
Let cool in pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Gently mix in cheese, broccoli and pasta.
Garnish with tomatoes.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Cut cranberries in half, add 1/4 cup sugar and set aside. Sift flour, soda, salt and 1/4 cup sugar together.
Add enough water to orange juice to make 1 cup.
Add grated orange peel, margarine and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Add nuts and cranberries.
Spoon into muffin pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Brown and drain the ground beef, onion and green pepper. In a crock-pot, combine remaining ingredients. Add meat mixture. Set crock-pot on low and cook for 6 to 8 hours. (You may also set crock-pot on high and cook for 3 to 4 hours instead.)

title: german potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients in pot.
Fill with cold water to cover. Keep water level covering vegetables until about 10 to 15 minutes before being done.
Continue cooking with water at 3/4 level.
Add salt to taste.
Add beef bouillon cubes to taste.
Cook at medium heat (do not boil) for 45 minutes or until done.
Mash with hand potato masher until just slightly lumpy.
Goes well with cornbread.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in loaf pan and bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroni fruit salad
directions: Mix alone and bring to boil the juices from pineapple and oranges, sugar, salt and flour.
Cook 1 box orzo #43 until tender; drain and rinse.
Do not mix until cold.
Mix cooked mixture and orzo.
Fold in pineapple, oranges and any other fruit desired. Add 1 (10-ounce) container of Cool Whip.
Decorate with cherries.

title: chili
directions: In large skillet, brown beef, onion, green pepper.
Drain excess fat.
Break up whole tomatoes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook in a Dutch oven at 350°until bubbly.
Stir to keep from burning.	If hotter chili desired, add hot peppers (bottled) and some of the pepper juice to suit your own taste. Serves 5 to 6 persons.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. This dish tastes better when it cools.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cube and cook chicken.
In medium saucepan, heat soup (do not add milk or water).
Stir in sour cream; stir until smooth. Reserve 1 cup of mixture.
Fill each tortilla with chicken, cheese, onion and soup mixture.
Roll up and place side-by-side in casserole dish.
Pour reserved soup mixture over top of tortillas. Heat uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with guacamole and olives.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add oil, vanilla and dry ingredients; blend well and chill.	Form in balls;
dip in sugar.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: turkey scallopini with cranberry sauce(healthy dinner)
directions: Pound turkey breasts between moistened sheets of wax paper to 1/4-inch thickness.
Combine lemon juice and oil.
Brush on both sides of cutlets.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to cook.

title: mrs. bond's dip
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender at high speed until well blended.
Add to one pint Hellmann's mayonnaise.

title: smothered steak
directions: Brown steak in baking pan.
Top with carrots, celery, onion, green pepper and potatoes.
Cover with can of stewed tomatoes. Cover pan with foil.
Bake in moderate oven for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mushroom pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops and season to taste.
Add water and soy sauce.
Slice onions and lay over chops (optional).
Add soup. Cover and cook on top of stove 1 hour.

title: carrot cassantro
directions: Peel and slice carrots; add sugar.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
In double boiler, melt butter, cheese, onions and Tabasco and cook until creamy.
Drain carrots; put in baking dish and pour cheese sauce over carrots.
Cover with crumbled crackers. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: "french salad" dressing
directions: Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: hot cheddar dip
directions: Mix and bake in casserole for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry cream roll
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add cold water, vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt and beat until smooth.
Pour into greased, waxed paper lined 11 x 14 pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Turn out onto tea towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Remove waxed paper.
Roll up cake while still warm.
Cool for 1 hour.
Spread with filling after unrolling.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Mix ground chuck, onion, toast, applesauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Press into baking dish.
Then mix brown sugar and catsup.
Spread over loaf and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix eggs, oil and buttermilk separately and pour over dry ingredients.
Fill muffin cups.
Cook at 400° for 15 minutes.
Mix will keep up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: fresh banana bundt cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Slowly add sugar.
Beat until light.
Add bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
In separate bowl, mix flour, soda and salt together.
Add to banana mixture and blend well.
Slowly add sour cream; beat until blended.
Pour in greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: veal or chicken marsala
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Coat meat and brown in 1/2 stick of butter.
Remove meat.
Add mushrooms and onion; saute until translucent in the other 1/2 stick of butter.
Add Marsala wine and meat; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
If sauce is thin, add remaining flour mixture. Serves 3 or 4.

title: easy carrot bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix 2 minutes on medium speed.
Spoon into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes, or until done.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a 3-quart baking dish, combine soup, water, rice, Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 can of French fried onions.
Arrange chicken on rice mixture.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Top with remaining French fried onions; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion and pepper and brown. Add other ingredients.
Bring to a boil for 3 or 4 minutes.
Good with ham or beef.

title: corned beef
directions: Place corned beef in roasting pan or large pot.
Cover with water.
Add all ingredients; cover and boil or bake in oven until tender.
Remove from liquid and cool.
Serve with cabbage and potatoes.

title: creme fraiche
directions: Shake heavy cream and buttermilk vigorously for one minute in a screw-top jar.
Let stand at room temperature for five or six hours, until cream is thickened to a thick rich texture between sweet and sour cream.
Refrigerate.
Will keep several days.
A wonderful topping.

title: celebration egg nog
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender at high speed.
Serve immediately.
Double or triple as needed.
Very rich.
Yields 1 quart.

title: snowflake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, egg and flavoring well.
Stir dry ingredients together and blend into shortening mixture.
Chill 1 hour.

title: noodle chowder
