directions: In a large pot combine the celery, squash, broccoli florets, onion and chicken broth.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare the pasta according to package directions and set aside.
Stir the milk, cheese, salt and pepper into the vegetable mixture.
Add the cooked noodles to the mixture and simmer for about 10 minutes until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jello according to package instructions. Grind all cranberries, orange, apple and nuts and add to jello. Add sugar and salt. Let set. Serves 6 to 8.

title: country casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion and drain well.
Add cream cheese, mushroom soup and vegetables.
Heat thoroughly.
Salt and pepper to taste.
This can be topped with biscuits and baked or served with noodles or rice.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown onion, celery, green pepper and hamburger in large skillet. Drain grease off. Add sausage, beans, tomato sauce and seasoning.
Heat. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or in crock-pot for 3 hours on high.

title: apple betty
directions: Mound apples in buttered 9 or 10-inch pie plate; sprinkle with orange juice.

title: pecan cheese balls
directions: Mix well; shape into cocktail size balls (1 tablespoon each). Brown in small amount of vegetable oil; drain.

title: meringue teasers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line metal pans with aluminum foil.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla. Beat together. Add chips and nuts. Stir by hand.
If food coloring is used, add now.
Spoon onto foil by teaspoon.
Turn off oven.
Put all pans in and close the door. Do not open door for 6 hours or cookies will fail.

title: trifle
directions: Slice angel food cake into 3 layers.
Dissolve gelatin according to directions on box.
Prepare pudding according to directions on package and add the drained fruit cocktail to the pudding as soon as it thickens.
Place one layer of cake in a large bowl; spoon the liquid gelatin over the cake, then a layer of the pudding and fruit cocktail mixture.
Repeat the steps with the other two layers of cake.
Spread the whipped cream on top and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Use a clear glass bowl to make this treat look more festive.

title: granny meriwether's fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat eggs, adding vanilla to beaten eggs.
Mix together all dry ingredients making sure mixture is smooth.
Add margarine and eggs to this mixture, stirring until blended well. Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Great served warm with ice cream!

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet, add onion, pepper and chicken. Cook until chicken is tender, stirring often. Add corn, broth and salsa; bring to a boil. Stir in rice and cover. Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Fluff with fork. Pour into serving dish, sprinkle with cheese and let stand 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: biscuitti
directions: Beat the eggs slightly. Gradually add sugar and oil. Mix well. Sift baking powder and flour together, and gradually add into mixture.
Add anise to the mixture.
Place the entire mix into a jelly roll sheet pan (or French bread loaf pan) and spread evenly.
Preheat oven to 350° and cook for 20 minutes. Cool.
Cut into slices and brown on each side at 400° for just a few minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Add 1 can O.C. French fried onions and bake 3 minutes more.

title: old-fashioned green beans and potatoes
directions: Fry bacon until golden.
Stir in beans, onion and water. Simmer 1 minute.
Stir well.
Add potatoes and cook until tender, about 15 minutes.

title: five minute fruit salad
directions: Take your prettiest bowl and chill in freezer for 1/2 hour.

title: caramel-topped applesauce cake(12 servings)
directions: Place the raisins in a saucepan.
Add enough water to cover. Bring to boiling.
Remove from heat; let stand until cool.
Drain off the water.
Toss the nuts with the 2 tablespoons flour; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat the butter or margarine for 30 seconds.
Add the sugar; beat until well combined.
Beat in applesauce.
In another bowl, combine the 2 1/2 cups flour with cinnamon, baking soda and nutmeg.
Add to beaten mixture, beating until just combined.
Stir in the raisins and nuts.
Turn batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 65 to 70 minutes, or until done.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan; let cool.
Prepare the Caramel Frosting; spoon over cake.

title: basic sweet pastry
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Blend or sift together flour, sugar and salt; cut in finely shortening and butter.
Combine egg and cold water and sprinkle over flour mixture and toss lightly with a fork to make a soft dough.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface and knead gently 6 or 7 times.
Roll to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut into 4 inch rounds and line medium sized muffin cups or tart pans with the pastry.
(Or place over inverted muffin cups, pleating to make pastry fit smoothly.)
Prick the pastry.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Fill as desired.
This makes 12 to 14 medium-sized shells.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix together cracker crumbs and 1/2 stick of butter.
Press into 8-inch pie plate.
Chill.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter. Spoon into crust.
Mix lightly beaten eggs with milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over onions.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: delicious chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in bowl.
In saucepan, put shortening, margarine, water and cocoa.
Bring to boil over low heat.

title: easy chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook fryer until tender; leave broth in boiler.
Debone chicken; put back in broth.
Add bouillon cubes; let simmer until cubes are dissolved.
Add spaghetti.
Cook until tender.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Cut meat into bite-sized pieces.
Brown meat and onions.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer in crock-pot on low for at least 5 hours or until meat strings apart.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook the sugar, water and cornstarch until thick, then add 3 tablespoons strawberry jello.
Pour over fresh strawberries in a cooked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.
Let set 2 hours.

title: easy barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Place under broiler; broil until tender, turning occasionally.

title: green garden dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.
The longer it chills, the better.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix mayo and vinegar; set aside.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour mayo and vinegar mixture over the ingredients. Chill overnight.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Clean mushrooms.
If small, leave whole.
If large, cut in half.
Place mushrooms in 5-quart Dutch oven with butter and onion.
Cover and cook over low heat for about 1/2 hour until tender and mushrooms have made their own juice.

title: german salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and onions real thin.
Mix vinegar, sugar, water and dill together and bring to boil about 30 seconds. Then pour over cucumbers and onions and refrigerate.
Makes about 1-quart.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage, drain.
Cool.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with bread slices.
Sprinkle sausage evenly over bread, then layer cheese. Mix milk with well beaten eggs, salt, pepper and dry mustard. Pour over layers in pan.
Cover pan and put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease loaf pan.
Dump contents of pineapple into bottom of loaf pan.
Top with cherries.
Dump cake mix on top of fruit (dry mixture only, do not mix as directed on the box of mix).
Top with pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Fun, quick and easy!
Amazingly delicious.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine the chicken and celery in a bowl.
Mix together the lemon juice, salt, onion and mayonnaise.
Mix with chicken and celery mixture.
Pour into a baking dish and top with the cheese and almonds. Crumble the potato chips on top. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cornflake macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and dry.
Fold in sugar gradually. Add flavoring, coconut, cornflakes and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a well-oiled baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° until delicately brown.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Heat tomato sauce in a large saucepan on low setting.
In the meantime, heat olive oil in frying pan on high.
Mix all remaining ingredients well.
Form into small balls and brown in frying pan. Place meatballs in sauce and heat for 3 hours on low setting. Makes about 1 1/2 dozen meatballs.

title: okra casserole
directions: Saute okra in bacon drippings over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes,
just
enough to get it all good and hot.
Turn out into a
quart greased casserole.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery
until
crisp-tender.
Layer vegetables over okra. Put water
chestnuts
in
casserole
with olives and mix with other vegetables.
Arrange
tomatoes
over
the
top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: green rice
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: raisin bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir in raisins.
In separate bowl, add eggs, milk and oleo.
Add to other mixture, stirring only until moistened.
Do not beat.
Pour into two 9 x 5 x 2-inch pans, greased.
Mix together the sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over top of mixture and swirl into mixture with knife.
Bake at 425° about 1 hour or until done.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot oil, cook celery and onion until tender-crisp, stirring occasionally. Stir in soup and milk.
In a 10 x 6-inch baking dish, place cheese, broccoli, water chestnuts and rice. Stir in soup mixture. Bake 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Makes 5 cups or 8 servings.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed. Drain. Combine rest of ingredients while macaroni is hot.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Delicious!

title: goup
directions: Brown meat and add seasonings.
Add mushroom soup and noodles. Cook 15 minutes and serve.

title: won tons
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain well.
Add soy sauce, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Fill won ton wrappers.
Fold and deep fry until brown.
These can also be baked in a 350° oven until brown and crispy.

title: memphis corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl until blended.
Pour into a 2 qt baking (9 x 13 inch glass) dish.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until lightly browned and set.

title: old fashioned batter bread
directions: You will need a 6 x 9-inch loaf pan.

title: split pea soup
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
Saute onions and carrots in drippings for about 10 minutes, stirring often.
Stir peas into water; add carrots and onions and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for one hour or longer, until tender.
Add salt and taste. Garnish with reserved bacon.
Freezes well.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: pork chop special
directions: Wash chops.
Put in slightly greased pan and top with all ingredients on each chop.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Remove cover (foil) and bake 15 minutes more at 325°.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and mix well. Add salt and soda with flour. Add nuts and mix into first part. Form into rolls and place in freezer until ready to cook. Slice and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add
cooking
oil
and
sugar. Sift together in mixing	bowl, flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Stir defrosted strawberries into
egg
and sugar mixture, then add sifted dry ingredients
and
mix until well blended.
Pour into 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch
greased
loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool
in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out on rack.

title: stickies
directions: Mix cake mix, nuts, 1 egg and margarine.
Mix well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then mix cream cheese, coconut, vanilla, 2 eggs and powdered sugar together and spoon over the first layer. Bake at 350° for at least 35 minutes (depending on your oven; cook until golden).

title: pot  roast
directions: Cut up roast into small pieces.
Salt and black pepper to desired taste.
Put in boiler with cut up onion and cover with water.
Cook until meat and onions are done.
Pour other ingredients into mixture and cook until well done.

title: marble cake
directions: This all for a cake mold of about 10 inches long (approximately 2-quarts volume).

title: hamburger - stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Add margarine and onion. Cook until onions are tender.
Add flour, salt, pepper and garlic; mix well.
Add mushrooms and cream of chicken soup.
Mix well and simmer on low heat, about 10 minutes.
Add sour cream and simmer another 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook noodles until done.
Serve stroganoff over noodles.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut up dates, pecans and orange slices.
Melt butter and pour over all the ingredients.
Let stand while preparing batter.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Layer
all
ingredients
beginning with macaroni, tuna, soup, milk, cheese and chips in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Serves 6.

title: homestyle canneloni
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown beef.
Add onion and saute until translucent.
Pour off fat.
Add spinach, 1 cup Mozzarella, bread crumbs, egg, 1/2 cheese and seasonings.
Mix well; set aside.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add sugar, milk, vanilla and peanut butter.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add oats.
Stir well.
Using a spoon, spoon the mixture on wax paper.
Be sure to make the cookies while the mixture is still hot.
You may want to use a knife or small spatula to take the mixture off the spoon.

title: crab and pasta primavera
directions: Saute zucchini in butter for 1 minute.
Add mushrooms and peas and saute for about 1 minute.
Add cream, cheese, basil and pepper and simmer about 1 minute.
Add crab; stir until heated and serve over the pasta.

title: gourmet rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven; mix well. Bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat to simmer.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in a small amount of water about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Add zucchini and onion.
Combine stuffing mix and margarine.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Spread zucchini mixture on top.
With spoon, slightly mix the two together.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over top.
Cover with foil or glass cover. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: my thousand island dressing
directions: Mix soup, brown sugar, mustard, vinegar, oil, catsup, lemon juice, paprika and celery seed thoroughly.
Add relish, pepper, onions and salad dressing.
Mix well and store in refrigerator. (You can use a blender.)

title: chocolate malt coffee creamer
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Stir well until blended.
Store in airtight container.
Use 2 heaping teaspoons in 8 ounces hot coffee.

title: creme coconut pie
directions: Mix well together and bake at 300° for 45 minutes in an unbaked pie shell.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thin.
Add onions, peppers and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt.
Cover with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours.
Drain.

title: pork pie
directions: Bake potato until done, 30 to 45 minutes in 400 degrees preheated oven. Peel and mash the potato. Place potato, ground pork, onion, spices and water in large frying pan. Simmer until very thick, for about 1 hour. Meanwhile, prepare your pastry. Line a deep-dish pie plate with pastry. Spoon in filling, spread evenly. Cover with top crust. Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with paprika, if desired. Cut steam vent. Bake for 50 minutes at 350 degrees. If edges brown too fast, cover with a strip of foil. Serve warm.

title: carrie's brunch casserole
directions: Crumble and cook sausage and drain well.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish with crescent rolls, pressing perforations to seal, which forms bottom crust for mixture.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and pepper together.
Put sausage and cheese onto crust.
Pour milk-egg mixture over all.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Remove and let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: baked potatoes and onions
directions: Slice onions and unpeeled potatoes.
Arrange in 3 rows in 9 x 13-inch baking dish, alternating potatoes and onion slices, overlapping slightly.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl.
Drizzle over potatoes and
onions.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 40 minutes. Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes longer.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Stir this all together to make one serving of hot chocolate. Mix 1/4 to 1/3 cup of the mix into a cup of hot water.
This makes excellent Christmas gifts in pretty decorated glass jars.
One batch will make several small jars full.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream the butter and cheese. Add salt and cayenne.
Work in flour.
Roll and cut or put through cookie press.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Do not overcook.
They freeze well.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream the shortening, eggs and sugar.
Mix others as given in order.
Mix cocoa in hot water and soda in milk. Bake 25 or 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fantastic salad
directions: Heat reserved juices to dissolve jello.
When cool, mix in cottage cheese.
Add orange sections, crushed pineapple and Cool Whip; mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: daube glace
directions: Spray large mold with Pam.
Place the sliced olives in mold and cover with shredded meat.
Dissolve 2 packages unflavored gelatin in 1 can of the beef consomme.
Add the second can of consomme, green onions, parsley, garlic, Worcestershire, Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Mix well and pour over the meat in the mold.
Refrigerate. Turn out on a dish and garnish.
To serve, slice.

title: mustard slices(club member: leslie jordan)
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Cut bread diagonally into 1-inch slices. Mix remaining ingredients. Spread on slices.
Reassemble loaf. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 15 minutes.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and egg.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in milk.
After baking mixture, melt butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake until golden brown.
Once done, remove and roll in butter and sugar mixture.
The butter allows the sugar and cinnamon to stick to muffin.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes average 12 muffins.

title: georgia's gorgeous peanut butter gems
directions: Melt in the top of a double boiler, semi-sweet chocolate pieces.
Mix together peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs, melted butter, xx sugar and vanilla.
Pat this into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread melted chocolate on top.
Chill and cut into small squares.

title: coca-cola salad recipe
directions: Mix
and refrigerate.
Great for holiday get togethers. Very easy to make.

title: noodles
directions: Mix.
Roll thin and place in the sun to dry.
Cut fine.
Put in boiling broth.
Cook 15 minutes slowly.

title: easy party dip
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve with vegetable dippers.

title: biscuit sloppy joes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
Brown ground beef in large skillet; drain.
Stir in Sloppy Joe mix, cook as directed.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, salt, cinnamon and oil.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add carrots and vanilla.
Pour into two greased 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool and frost.

title: cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix together.
Fill paper cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
They sink in the middle while cooling.
Fill with pie filling (cherry, strawberry, pineapple or blueberry).

title: minty mixed melon
directions: Mix fruit, lime peels and lime juice together.
Chill 1 hour and serve.

title: banana split pie
directions: In a pie dish, layer in order listed.
Chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Break or cut cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces. Shred carrots.
Drain olives and water chestnuts.
Mix vegetables, olives and water chestnuts with salad dressing.
Chill at least 8 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: apple puff pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place a 12-inch skillet in oven to heat. (Note:
if your skillet handle isn't ovenproof, wrap handle tightly with foil to avoid burning.)
Meanwhile, make batter.
In a medium size bowl, use an electric mixer to beat eggs until frothy, then beat in flour, milk and salt on medium speed for about 1 minute. Remove skillet from oven.
Add butter, then swirl skillet until butter melts and coats all sides of the pan.
In a small bowl, mix sugar and cinnamon.
Toss with apple slices in skillet.
Pour batter over the apples (can also make without apples or without sugar on apples) in skillet.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes or until pancake is puffy and golden brown.
Makes 1 large pancake that serves 4.

title: egg salad cheese spread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Yields 3 cups.

title: watercress and avocado salad
directions: Make a bed of watercress sprigs on individual salad plates. Top with half an avocado.
Fill the avocado with generous dollop of Cashew Mayonnaise with sweet basil.
Sprinkle with paprika or use pimento strips for garnish.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite size pieces. Cut grapes in half.
Dice onion. Fry bacon and crumble.
Mix all ingredients.

title: chicken rice roger
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Flour and brown chicken. Place rice, salt and pepper in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole and add onion and mushrooms (juice and all).
Place chicken on top. Pour bouillon over and dot with margarine.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pastrami dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, onion, green pepper and garlic salt.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes to blend well.
Serve with fresh veggies or crackers.
Wonderful both warm or cold.

title: double diamond brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 200 degrees.
Coat an 8 x 11 x .5 inch baking pan with non-stick spray.
Pulse Graham Crackers into crumbs in a food processor, or place in a large plastic bag and crush with a rolling pin.
Yield 2 c. crumbs.
Mix in a small bowl Crumbs, Cocoa and salt, mix well and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl combine Eggs, Egg White, Brown Sugar and Granulated Sugar.
Beat with electric mixer on high until thickened (about 2 minutes).
Blend in Coffee Granules and Vanilla.
Gently fold in Dates.
Chocolate Chips and cracker mixture.
Scrape batter into prepared baking dish, spread evenly.
Bake Brownies for 25-30 minutes or until top springs back when gently touched.
Let Cool completely in the pan on a wire rack before cutting.

title: fluffy pancakes
directions: Measure flour.
Add sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir well. Combine egg yolks, milk and butter.
Add to dry ingredients. Beat with beater until smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour 1/3 cup batter for each pancake on hot griddle.
Grease griddle lightly for first pancake only.
Makes 12 five-inch pancakes.

title: mrs. herman johnson's pecan millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in 1 tablespoon milk on low heat.
Melt chocolate on separate heat and mix with wax.
Form caramel and nuts into balls and coat with chocolate-wax mixture.
Freeze 1/2 hour.
Makes 100.

title: barb's best baked beans(microwave recipe)
directions: Combine bacon and green pepper in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook at High 3 to 4 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, at High, 3 to 4 minutes, then at Medium-low, 10 to 12 minutes.
(Best if prepared day before planned serving time, for flavors to blend.)

title: loretta's cheesecake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bake in oven for 8 to 10 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool before putting filling on.

title: egg drop soup
directions: In medium saucepan, combine soup and water.
Bring to boil; simmer 2 minutes.
Quickly stir beaten egg into soup with a fork until it separates and shreds.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil butter, sugar, Karo syrup and salt for 5 minutes.
Add soda and stir.
Pour mixture over popped corn.
Add peanuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Put on waxed paper to cool.

title: dough for rolls(nut or apricot)
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cans of scalded milk and margarine; take off fire and add 1 1/2 cans cold water.
Take cakes of yeast and put in 1 cup warm water until yeast comes to top.
Mix all together until dough comes off your hand.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Wet a towel to cover dough.

title: moist corn bread squares
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix with wire whisk.
Add eggs, milk and oil.
Beat with whisk or spoon just until moistened.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until bread tests done.
Cut in squares and serve with butter and favorite jelly.

title: vegetable kabobs
directions: Cut up your favorite vegetables or whatever someone gives you. Place your vegetables on small skewers.
Melt margarine with lemon juice.
Baste vegetables and grill 10 to 12 minutes on high. You can also add leftover meat or fruit (bananas or pineapple).

title: raw vegie pizza
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Separate dough and pat into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill and onion.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with vegies.
Cut and serve.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts in a large bowl; beat until blended.
Stir in the nuts.
Drop from a spoon onto a greased cookie sheet using about 2 tablespoons of dough for each. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 15 to 17 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Makes 5 dozen large cookies.

title: beef roast with vegetables
directions: Brown beef in frying pan in butter or margarine on both sides. Put in pot and boil until tender.
Remove beef and put the remaining ingredients in broth.
Add water to broth until it covers vegetables.
After vegetables are done, return beef to pot and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: fried fish or shrimp
directions: Heat oil (1 1/2-inch) in heavy saucepan or deep fryer to moderately high (350°).
Lightly coat fish with salt.
Mix 1 cup Bisquick mix, salt, egg and buttermilk until smooth (could add more buttermilk if not smooth). Dip fish into batter, letting excess batter drip back into bowl.
Fry until golden brown, about 7 minutes on each side. Drain excess oil from fish and serve.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer 10 minutes over medium heat.
Dunk Frankfurters or use on other meats.

title: lazy day pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add milk and raisins.
Put into a well-greased baking dish.
Pour the following sauce over top of batter:
1 cup brown sugar, 1 tablespoon butter, 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable latkas
directions: Rinse and drain shredded potatoes twice with cold water. Squeeze dry and put in a large bowl.
Add shredded carrots, zucchini, parsnip, scallions and salt.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir flour, egg yolks and pepper into vegetable mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold into batter.
Heat nonstick griddle over medium heat until hot. Lightly grease griddle with 1 teaspoon oil per batch of pancakes.

title: chili mac
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In bowl of a Regal food processor, using S-blade, mix flour, powdered sugar and salt.
Pulse several times to mix well.
Cut hard butter into 1/4-inch slices.
With processor running, drop butter slices into flour mixture.
Process only until fine crumb stage.
Press evenly into greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: date and nut pie
directions: Mix together the dates, nuts, saltines and sugar.
Beat 3 egg whites until stiff.
Add 1 teaspoon almond flavoring.
Blend with the date and nut mixture.
Pour in well buttered pie dish.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and top with whipped cream. Cool Whip may be substituted.
Delicious!

title: kings hawaiian bread
directions: Remove center from bread.
Mix all other ingredients in order. Stir well; pour into center of bread.

title: banana pudding
directions: Stir milk and Cool Whip in pudding mix.
Make layers of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
Makes a big pan.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy orange pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Gradually add softened cream cheese and blend well (I put this in blender).
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Add syrup to jello with orange and lemon juice and blend well.

title: butter cake
directions: Cream
margarine. Slowly add sugar.
Cream well.
Add 6 eggs (one at a time)
beating
well.
Stir
in sour cream; mix the flour and soda together and add the flour and soda mixture to the creamed mixture, 1/2
at
a time.
Stir in the vanilla. Pour into greased and floured
pan.
Bake
1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine sugar, salad dressing and vinegar.
Mix long enough for the sugar to be absorbed.
Toss with the rest of the ingredients; chill and enjoy.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine 2 packages of stuffing mix with enough broth to moisten.
Set aside 1/3 of this mixture.
Spread remainder in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer chicken over stuffing mixture. Combine 1/2 to 3/4 cup of broth with 2 cans of soup.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Then crumble remainder of stuffing mix over top. Bake at 375° for 20-25 minutes or until brown.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Sift the flours together.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at at time.
Gradually add flour and flavorings.

title: apple stir about
directions: Beat the eggs well and add the sugar and salt slowly.
Beat until the sugar is dissolved.
Add the flour, baking powder and beat until smooth.
Add the finely chopped apples.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch dish and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: In saucepan over medium-high heat, melt 1/4 cup spread.
Blend in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and begins to boil.
Cook and stir one minute.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Combine cheese sauce and macaroni in 2 quart casserole dish.
Melt remaining spread; stir in cracker crumbs. Sprinkle on casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Make meatballs bite size.
Brown on low heat; drain off excess fat.
Simmer in sauce 15 minutes.

title: special pumpkin roll
directions: Mix
the
sugar,
pumpkin and eggs well.
Add the soda, salt, cinnamon
and flour.
Line jelly-roll pan with powdered sugared wax
paper. Spread batter with spatula. Bake for 15 to 18 minutes at 375°.
Cool for 5 minutes. Turn cake on dampened towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Remove waxed paper. Roll cake. Let
cool
completely,
then unroll and fill with Cream Cheese Filling.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Cream butter; add warm applesauce.
Add sour milk in which soda has been dissolved.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Add fruits and nuts which have been dredged in flour.
Add coconut and grated orange rind.
Pour into well-greased and floured cake pan or 5 (1-pound) tins.
Bake in very moderate oven (305° to 325°) about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet. Salt and pepper to taste; drain. Put tomato sauce, water, chili mix, beans and some broken spaghetti noodles in pan. Add ground beef and mix.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add remaining ingredients, except hot dogs.
Cook until smooth and creamy.
Add hot dogs and cook until hot dogs are puffy.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix food coloring with cocoa; let set. Cream the Crisco, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat hard. Add cocoa mixture and mix well. Alternate adding flour and salt with buttermilk. Add soda and beat. Add vinegar and beat hard. Bake in 2 (9-inch) layer pans at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: After mixing first 4 ingredients, sift together and fold in last 6 ingredients; mix well.
Line 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan with waxed paper.
Spread dough evenly and sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out onto towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Remove wax paper.
Begin at narrow end of cake rolling towel and cake together.
After completely cooling, unroll and spread filling over cake.
Re-roll and chill.

title: tomato, cucumber and onion salad
directions: In a large bowl, dice or cut tomatoes and slice onions and cucumber.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Blend, then cover and refrigerate a few hours.

title: honey dijon ham
directions: Cook ham at 325° for 15 minutes per pound.
Cook 1 1/2 hours, then glace it.
Score diamonds in top.
Coat generously.

title: 7 layer lettuce salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken herb casserole
directions: Combine cooked chicken, onions and celery.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, vinegar, milk, flavoring and eggs, then add coconut. Put in unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes then 325° until done. Makes 2 (10-inch) pies or 3 (9-inch) pies.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Combine with the other ingredients, reserving 1 1/2 cups pecans. Form into 2 balls. Roll in remaining chopped nuts. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate until firm.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Combine ingredients except vanilla in upper part of double boiler.
Beat well.
Place over boiling water and beat constantly with rotary beater 7 minutes. Remove from fire and continue beating until frosting stands up in peaks.
Add vanilla and frost your
cake.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in double boiler and boil until rice is tender, about 1/2 hour to 1 hour or more.
Beat 1 egg and add 1/2 cup milk.
Stir in the first mixture.
Very good.

title: hawaiian chops
directions: Brown chops in hot fat; season.
Place pineapple on each chop.
Add carrots.
Add water; cover and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn tortillas
directions: In a bowl, add flour and salt and mix very well.
Then add water, a little at a time, while mixing.
Take dough in hands and form into an elastic dough.
Knead thoroughly; add more water, if necessary to keep dough moist.
Dough should hold its shape but still be moist.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add cornmeal and blend well.
Add lemon juice and rind (at least 1/3 cup juice).
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: iced ritz crackers
directions: Cook milk and dates slowly until thick.
Let cool and add some chopped nuts.
Put on Ritz crackers and place on cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool. Ice with frosting of:

title: mushroom chicken
directions: In 2-quart casserole, add mushroom and celery soups and mix. Place rinsed chicken in soup mixture.
Sprinkle onion/mushroom Recipe Secrets on top.
Add 1/2 cup water or chicken broth.

title: the twelve days of christmas
directions: Make jello with water.
When chilled, add pineapple.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Grind the bell pepper and red hot pepper.
Mix all ingredients together. Cook to slow rolling boil. Remove from stove and cool 15 minutes. Add 1 bottle Certo.
Seal while still hot. Serve on crackers topped with cream cheese and jelly.

title: autumn fruit cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, then add vanilla.
Mix all other ingredients; mix well.
Put cake in cool oven; bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crunchy fish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In pie plate, mix lemon juice, chili powder and half of melted margarine.
On waxed paper, place crushed crackers.
Dip fish fillets into chili powder mixture, then into crackers to coat. Place fillets in baking dish.
Drizzle with remaining melted margarine.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until fish flakes easily.

title: creamy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in	salted	water
until
tender,
12 to 15 minutes.
Drain well.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Melt 3/4 stick of butter in frying pan.
Add stuffing and spice and mix well. Pack some in
bottom
of
casserole. Reserve some for topping. Pour squash
mixture over stuffing.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Put remaining
oleo
on top.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: harvard beets(microwave)
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
In 1 cup glass measure, pour beet liquid and add enough water to make 1 cup of liquid.
In 1-quart microproof casserole or bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Stir in hot liquid.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens and is clear.
Add beets and stir gently.
Cook, covered, on High about 5 minutes or until beets are hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate no bake cookies(yields 50 servings)
directions: Melt butter.
Add milk, sugar, cocoa and peanut butter.
Cook 1 minute to boiling point.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool and serve.

title: "pink salad"
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cool whip and fold in.
Add cottage cheese and fruit. Best made just before serving. May be stored in refrigerator uncovered.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 24 hours, stirring several times.
Serve.
Store in airtight container.

title: million dollar cake
directions: Heat oven.
Get utensils and ingredients.

Remove blocks and toy auto from table. Grease pan. Crack nuts. Measure 2 cups flour; remove Jonathon's hands from flour; wash flour off him. Re-measure flour; put flour, salt and baking powder in sifter. Get dust pan and brush up pieces of bowl Jonathon knocked on the floor. Get another bowl; answer the door bell. Return to kitchen. Remove Jonathon's hand from bowl. Wash Jonathon; grease another pan; answer the telephone. Return to kitchen; find Jonathon. Remove one hammer from bowl. Take up greased pan and find layer of nut shells in it. Head for Jonathon, who flies, knocking bowl off table. Wash kitchen floor, table walls and dishes.
Call bakery. Lie down!

title: clubhouse lemonade
directions: In large pitcher, combine lemon juice and sugar.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.

title: english pea salad
directions: Combine peas, celery, cheese, olives, onion and eggs in a mixing bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir until smooth. Add to pea mixture, stir to combine.
Serve chilled.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Makes 4 pie crusts.
Combine Crisco, flour and salt.
In small bowl, mix egg, water and vinegar.
Add to flour mixture, mixing well until dough forms a ball.
Chill 15 minutes.
Divide dough into four balls and roll out on well floured board.

title: cheese bread
directions: Melt margarine in pot.
Add mayonnaise and stir until mixed. Add cheese and garlic powder; stir until melted.
Add green onions.
Cut bread in half and coat each half with mixture.
Place on a baking pan open faced and bake at 350° until top is brown.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Separate rolls and place on pizza pan.
Spread with fingers and seal seams.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 19 minutes; cool.
Mix sour cream, horseradish and salt and pepper.
Blend until smooth. Spread over crust.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Cut into appetizer pieces.
Makes about 60.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and spread on French bread cut in half or on hamburger buns.
Put on heavy foil and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: new england baked beans(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Cover beans with water and soak overnight. In the morning, boil beans in same water until fork-tender (approximately 20 to 30 minutes). Drain and transfer beans to a crock-pot set on low. Cover beans with 4 to 5 slices of salt pork and a peeled medium onion (whole or cut in half). Mix together molasses, salt and dry mustard with boiling water and add to beans. Cover beans with liquid and keep covered throughout cooking time. Add boiling water if beans start to dry out. Continue to cook on low for 7 to 10 hours. Do not stir during cooking.

title: arizona mountain soup
directions: Rinse beans.
In 5-quart kettle, combine beans and 3 cups water.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Do not drain.
Simmer, covered, 2 hours or until beans are tender; drain, reserving 2 cups liquid.
In kettle, cook bacon until crisp.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook and stir until tender but not brown.
Stir in beans, tomatoes, rice, salt, paprika and pepper.
Add reserved bean liquid and 2 cups water.
Bring to boil and simmer 1 hour.
If too thick, add water.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, butter and evaporated milk to a boil for 5 minutes.
Take off stove and add peanut butter, marshmallow
and vanilla.
Mix with beater.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: mexican pie
directions: Brown and drain ground meat.
Add remaining ingredients, except shredded cheese.
Place mixture in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve with chips and salad.

title: grandma's green beans
directions: Put water on to boil in pan big enough for all ingredients. Cook
bacon
but do not crisp (barely cook), drain fat. Add prepared green beans and put lid on and steam for approximately 6 to 8 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add boiling water and remaining
ingredients.
Simmer
for
to
2 hours. Enjoy!

title: egg custard
directions: Mix well and pour in greased and floured 8-inch pie pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Carefully partially slice potatoes; lay a spoon to side to prevent cutting all the way through. Place in baking dish. Gently separate slices. Salt and pepper. Use herbs here. Bake at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes. Sprinkle with both cheeses and bake 10 minutes more. Should be lightly browned and cheese melted.

title: tuna spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, adjusting amounts as needed for desired consistency.
A firmer spread made be placed in a mold and chilled.
A softer spread may be used without additional chilling.
Serve with crackers or toast rounds.

title: beef and cabbage soup
directions: Cook cabbage, potatoes, onions and green pepper covered with water until tender.
After cooked, drain well.
Brown ground beef in frying pan and drain grease.
Mix tomatoes, water, Veg-All and seasonings together.
Add cooked mixture.
Let simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: In top of double boiler, combine water, brandy, gelatin, 1/2 cup sugar and chocolate.
Heat until mixture is smooth and well blended.
Remove from heat and allow mixture to cool until it mounds with a spoon (stir frequently with a wire whisk).
While chocolate mixture is cooking, beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add cream of tartar and gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar, beat until stiff peaks form; set aside.

title: crepes ensenada
directions: In a 2 qt. pan, gently melt the butter, stir in the flour and cook for a minute or two until the butter and flour start to come together in a ball around the pan. Do not brown. A little at a time add the milk, allowing the sauce to thicken between additions, keep stirring. When all of the milk has been added, stir in the cheddar, mustard, salt, pepper and paprika. Set aside. Put one slice of Monterray Jack cheese, one slice of ham and one chili in the middle of a tortilla. Roll up and secure with a toothpick. Place in a greased pan, side by side, seam side down. Pour over the prepared cheese sauce and bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for 45 minutes.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef, adding all seasoning.
Pour enough oil in skillet to just cover bottom.
Allow oil to get hot, then place a tortilla shell in long enough to get really soft, then turn over and do other side.
Put a large spoon of refried beans, hamburger meat and cheese in middle of flat tortilla.
Roll up ends.
Then roll sides up and place in a sprayed pan (Pam).
Pour enchilada sauce over top and add shredded cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In medium size mixing bowl, mix all ingredients together, stirring well until blended.
Spoon put onto baking pan and cook 8 minutes at 400 degrees on top rack in oven.

title: copper pennies
directions: Layer carrots, onion and bell pepper in a large dish.
Mix remaining ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables and chill.
Will keep in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Break bread into bite size pieces.
Layer bread, sausage and cheese in greased casserole dish.
Pour egg and milk mixture over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 6.
Serve with sliced tomatoes and cantaloupe.

title: mom and dad's chili(chili cook off entry - 1994)
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add to pot the remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 hours and taste.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder, if desired.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: aunt cleo's macaroni delight
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Top with Ritz crackers.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 375° oven.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Sprinkle sugar over top after baked and while hot.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well in order given.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes (don't overbake).
If desired, you may add chopped nuts to the mixture.

title: jar slaw
directions: Process vegetables.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Pack in sterile jars and seal.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Add milk.
In saucepan, cook over low heat until hot.
Slightly beat egg yolks.
Slowly add to flour mixture.
Cook slowly until thick.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (9-inch) and bake at 350° until crust begins to brown. Top with meringue and continue baking until meringue is nicely browned.

title: simple hamburger casserole
directions: Cut up potatoes and boil until almost done.
Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Add corn, potatoes (liquid and all) and bouillon cube to hamburger and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip reese's cups
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; mix together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan to form crust.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt morsels in microwave on low heat, stirring every 30 seconds.
When melted, add peanuts.
Stir until cool enough to hold its shape when dropped by tablespoons onto waxed paper. Chill for 1 hour and remove from paper.

title: date appetizers
directions: Cut bacon strips in half; wrap around dates.
Secure with toothpick.
Broil until bacon is cooked crisp.
Turn often.

title: quick kolacky
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Knead until dough is smooth.
Roll out over powdered sugar.
Cut into 3-inch squares and fill with filling of choice.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: nona's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt in pan.
Add enough water to make a paste.
Beat in egg yolks.
Add remaining water, milk, vanilla and butter.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell. Cover with meringue.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add all remaining ingredients, except powdered sugar. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool on rack and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix together, put in dish.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Put all vegetables through food chopper.
Put in cloth and squeeze until dry.
Add chopped eggs; salt to taste and add mayonnaise.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, syrup, salt, margarine, milk, vanilla and chopped pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until nearly firm in the center.

title: chicken baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Brown slowly on both sides in skillet in 1 tablespoon hot oil.
Place pork chops in following sauce:
soup, milk and water.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix together and roll out thin on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 325°.

title: vegetable spread
directions: Chop all ingredients very fine and drain.
Mix with softened cream cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Add just enough mayonnaise to spread well.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix celery, bell pepper, onion and pimento in small bowl.
Mix potatoes and boiled eggs in large bowl, then mix with celery, etc. Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Toss until well mixed.

title: green tomato mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix.
Drop on greased baking sheet by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° until brown (10 to 15 minutes).

title: drop biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix dry ingredients together. Add buttermilk. Mix well. After dropping biscuits on greased baking sheet, brush tops of biscuits with bacon grease. Put in oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until tops of biscuits are golden brown. Makes 6 biscuits.

title: lemon-pineapple jello
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water in top of double boiler. Stir in marshmallows until dissolved.
Remove from heat and beat in cream cheese and juice from pineapple; cool slightly.
Blend in Cool Whip and pineapple.
Chill until firm.
Makes a nice mold.

title: beef tamales
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and shortening to make batter. Add beef and mix well.
Place tablespoon on foil.
Roll 3 times. Fold ends.
Boil for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter ball
directions: Mix together well.
Form into balls.
Dip balls into melted dark chocolate almond bark.

title: marshmallow delights
directions: Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in small dish.
Dip marshmallows into butter.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar and place on triangles, sealing all edges.
Dip tops of dough in butter, then in sugar and cinnamon.
Place sugar side up in greased muffin pan.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Blend the peanut butter and confectioners sugar together.
Pat peanut butter mixture firmly into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt the chocolate chips with butter; pour over peanut butter.
Chill overnight.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chopped chicken in a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish or two 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch dishes.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Pam baking dish.
Place a layer of pork chops in bottom of dish.
Mix all other ingredients, using 1/2 can soup.
Put mixture on top of layer of pork chops.
Top with remainder of pork chops. Pour other 1/2 can of soup over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: fruit-nut cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder into bowl.
Cut up fruits, dates and nuts into it; stir.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar to yolks, then brandy and vanilla. Combine the two mixtures well.
Last, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: prune pudding cake
directions: Cream Wesson oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk and prunes.
(Do not use electric mixer.)
Beat until well blended.
Fold in chopped nuts, if desired.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan which has been well-greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and add the Prune Cake Topping.

title: fruit log
directions: Cut fruit in small pieces.
Chop nuts.
Mix fruit and nuts together with Eagle Brand milk and crushed vanilla wafers.
Shape into logs and roll in confectioners sugar.
Refrigerate.
When firm, cut into slices.
Makes 5 rolls.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Steam broccoli 2 minutes.
Chill in ice water.
Mix all together.
Chill and serve.

title: eudy cube steak
directions: Lightly bread the pieces of cube steak and fry with Pam only until outside of meat is brown.
Take meat out of pan.
Add soup mix, 2 1/2 cups water, cornstarch and salt and pepper to taste to pan with drippings.
Stir until brown.
Put steak in a casserole dish; pour soup mixture over and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300°. Great with potatoes!

title: marshmallow fudge brownies
directions: Mix together brownie ingredients and pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and place the marshmallows on top of brownies.
Press down slightly so they won't rise when frosting is put on.

title: green beans and chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in salt, garlic, ginger, turmeric and ajwain.
In a pot, heat some oil and braise green beans with the onions, green chilies, and potatoes for a few minutes.
Now add the chicken and saute until lightly browned.
Add 1/2 cup water and cook, covered over low heat until chicken is tender, stirring a few times.
When chicken is almost done, add the 2 Tbsp. chopped onion and cook a few more minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as per package directions.
Drain and add celery, onion, chestnuts, cheese and mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pineapple-banana pie(sugar-free)
directions: Cook pudding with pineapple juice and milk, then add sugar substitute.
When it thickens, remove from heat.
Add drained pineapple and vanilla; mix well.
Slice banana over
cooked crust. Pour pudding over sliced banana.
Dot with lite Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: kraut salad
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar; pour over other ingredients.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dip fish into batter and fry.

title: shrimp soup -- lo-fat
directions: Cook pasta according to directions; drain.
In a saucepan, combine 3 cups water, chicken bouillon and salt.
Bring to a boil. Stir in mushrooms and corn.
Reduce heat; cook, uncovered, until vegetables are tender.
Combine cornstarch and remaining water until smooth.
Stir into soup; bring to a boil.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Reduce heat; add the lettuce, shrimp, green onions, teriyaki sauce and spaghetti.
Let mixture heat thoroughly.
You can double recipe.

title: corn country green beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet. Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Add corn and beans and heat through.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Top with crumbled bacon.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix juice with flour and sugar.
Add 2/3 cup of cheese.
Place pineapple in buttered dish.
Pour mixture over pineapple.
Top with 2/3 cup cheese.
Top with buttered crumbs, then rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Cream sugar
and Crisco in big mixing bowl; add boiling water. Stir
until Crisco is melted; add cold water which has yeast dissolved
in
it.	Add
salt.
Beat
eggs	and
add
to mixture. Add
flour,
making
soft
dough slowly.
Cover with greased paper and
put in refrigerator for 1 or 2 hours.
Let rise about 2 hours and bake in moderate oven.

title: bongo biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Stir until mixed.
Spoon into a greased muffin pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400°
for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Makes 10 biscuits.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together Ro-Tel, soups and chicken broth.
Set aside.
Layer chicken, then soup mixture, then tortillas in greased 2-quart casserole.
Add onion.
Repeat layers and onion.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Set aside for 15 minutes, then serve.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mustard.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and stir until thickened.
In buttered casserole, place layers of potatoes, onion, and cheese sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until tender.

title: "schee" or russian cabbage soup
directions: Heat stock in large kettle.
Saute onion, carrots and celery in butter and turn into hot stock, adding bay leaf, dill, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and simmer until tender.

title: mary anne's vegetable dip
directions: Add all together and mix well and enjoy.

title: honey pineapple oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine undrained pineapple, oats and raisins in bowl; set aside.
Beat margarine and honey until blended and smooth in large mixing bowl.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Beat reserved pineapple mixture until blended.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg in medium bowl.
Add to pineapple mixture and beat until blended.
Drop by heaping tablespoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: lemon grape-nuts pudding
directions: Cream the butter and gradually add the sugar.
Add the egg yolks and beat until light and fluffy.
Combine the flour, Grape-Nuts and salt and stir into the creamed mixture.
Add the milk, lemon juice and rind.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in buttered casserole or dish or custard cups. Set in a pan of hot water.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until set.
Chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add Karo syrup, sugar and butter.
Stir in vanilla. Line bottom of a 9-inch pie crust with pecans.
Pour mixture over pecans and bake at 275° for 1 hour or until done.
(Can bake at 300° to 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.)

title: chocolate torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together flour, margarine and pecans. Pat evenly into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Allow crust to cool. Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread evenly over cooled crust. Mix together the chocolate and vanilla pudding with the milk. Spread over cream cheese layer. Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding. Top with chocolate decorations if desired.

title: vegi salad
directions: Mix and pour over vegi mixture.
Cover and chill overnight. Will last up to 6
weeks.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Add vanilla and salt after chocolate is melted.
Cream shortening and sugar and beaten egg yolks.
Add 3/4 cup of buttermilk alternating with sifted flour.
Dissolve soda in remaining 1/4 cup buttermilk and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in three 9-inch pans for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together both sugars and four eggs.
Add Wesson oil and vanilla, then flour and oatmeal, then chocolate morsels and pecans.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Pour Micro-Roux into heavy pot over medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp.
Bring to a boil, then add shrimp and simmer about 10 minutes, uncovered.
Stir, cover, turn off heat and let set about 15 minutes or more.
Serve over fluffy rice (serves 6) with Jazzed-Up French Bread, steamed broccoli and Sensation Salad.

title: spicy pecan muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 medium muffin cups.
Mix all ingredients, except sugar.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Fill muffin cups approximately 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons sugar.
Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: nachos
directions: Combine cheese cubes and milk in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Place chips in bowl and spoon mixture to taste over chips.
Top with tomato, avocados, olive slices and salsa to taste.

title: chocolate wiggles
directions: Mix together and bring to boil the sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Drop by slightly rounded teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Chill until firm.

title: mushroom rice casserole
directions: Heat the butter in a skillet. Saut the mushrooms and onions for 3 to 5 minutes, then stir in the rice and saut for 3 minutes longer, stirring constantly. Stir in the soup and consomm. Pour the mixture into a greased casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Check the rice after 30 minutes; if it is drying out, add a little boiling water.

title: fig souffle
directions: Blend well, mashing the cookies.

Fold in 3 stiffly beaten egg whites and pour into a quart and a half greased baking dish. Place dish in pan of hot water and bake 50 minutes at 375°. Serve warm or cold with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square baking dish.
Mix Bisquick, 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons cocoa in mixing bowl. Stir in milk and vanilla until well blended; pour in baking dish.

title: banana muffins(fat free)
directions: Spray 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups with cooking spray.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
In large bowl, using a fork or wire whisk, beat egg whites lightly.
Stir in mashed bananas, milk and corn syrup.
Add flour mixture; stir until well blended.
Spoon into prepared muffin cups.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove; cool on wire rack.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Mix all ingredients into a crock-pot.
Brown hamburger meat, drain and add to mixture.
Cook on high approximately 3 to 4 hours or on slow overnight.
Makes a bunch of stew.

title: santa's cornbread
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt; fold in cornbread.
Add all ingredients, mixing well!
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Mix cheese and pineapple together.
Save juice and mix sugar and flour to juice.
Place cheese and pineapple into dish.
Pour juice mixture over this.
Crumble 1 pack of Ritz crackers on top of this and melt 1 stick of butter and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat broccoli until thawed.
Mix all ingredients, except crackers.
Spoon into casserole; cover with crackers.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: mock pheasant
directions: Mix soup and milk. Roll strips in flour and brown in skillet. Transfer to large casserole. Cover with soup and milk.
Mix together.
Bake at 275° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Great with mashed potatoes or rice.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.

title: the marshall's popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine butter and oil in a small saucepan.
Heat until butter is melted. Set aside.
Place eggs and milk in mixing bowl. Beat with rotary beater until blended and frothy. Sift dry ingredients and add to milk-egg mixture.
Beat with rotary beater to a smooth batter.
Briefly reheat butter and oil, and using a pastry brush, grease hot popover pans.
(Muffin pan may also be used.)
Fill greased pan 1/3 full with batter. Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake final 10 minutes.
Makes 8 popovers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 can soup, bread crumbs, egg, onion and salt.
Shape firmly into loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375°.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish (9 x 9-inch).
Mix all ingredients, except fruit together.
Pour batter into baking dish. Pour peaches over top of batter. Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes. (My family likes batter mixture doubled.)

title: jim's crab bisque
directions: In a heavy skillet, melt butter; stir in flour.
Stir constantly while cooking on very low heat (cook about 2 minutes); don't brown.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients (all except crabmeat) and cook 3 to 4 minutes on low heat, until thickened (consistency should be that of potato soup).
Add crabmeat and simmer 5 minutes.
Garnish each serving with a parsley sprig.
Yields 4 cups.

title: mexican tea balls(russian wedding cakes)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, pecans and vanilla.
Roll into balls (size of walnuts).
Bake at 350° until light brown. Roll in powdered sugar immediately.
Allow to cool, then roll in powdered sugar again.

title: potato casserole
directions: Use butter to grease 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Combine all other ingredients, then spread in casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: peppermint brownie meltaways
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownies as directed on package, except stir coconut and nuts into batter.
Bake as directed. Cool.

title: chicken and shrimp fettuccine
directions: Cut chicken breasts in halves crosswise, then into 1/2-inch thick strips.
Slice spinach.
Cut mushrooms in quarters.
Prepare fettuccine as label directs; drain.
Keep warm.
Toss chicken, shrimp, sherry, cornstarch, ginger, salt and pepper; set aside.
In saucepan, heat oil over high heat.
Add mushrooms and soy sauce to boil.
Reduce heat.
Add meat mixture; stir quickly.
Simmer for 5 minutes, or until done.
Serve.

title: shadow ranch barbecued beans
directions: Heat the oven to 300°.
Peel the onion and chop into small pieces.
Melt margarine in a saucepan over very how heat.
Grease bottom and sides of a baking dish. Put onion pieces, melted margarine, pork and beans, dry mustard, sugars, catsup and Worcestershire sauce in the baking dish and mix well.
Sprinkle this mixture with salt and pepper.
Cover the dish. Bake for 2 hours.
Serve with applesauce, hot or cold.
Makes 8 portions.

title: lite chocolate mousse
directions: In small saucepan, combine skim milk and gelatin; let stand until gelatin is softened, about 1 minute.
Stir over low heat about 5 minutes until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat; add cocoa, Sweet 'N Low, stirring until dissolved; stir in 1 cup evaporated skim milk and vanilla.
Pour into a large bowl; refrigerate 2 hours until mixture is syrup-like consistency.
In a large bowl with an electric mixer, beat remaining 1/2 cup chilled evaporated skim milk on high speed about 4 minutes until stiff peaks form.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Spoon into 4 individual dessert glasses.
Chill until firm, about 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well with mayonnaise. Best when made ready to eat. Chill if made in advance. Serves 5 to 6.

title: mayonnaise devil's food cake
directions: Dissolve soda in water.
Pour all ingredients in bowl.
Beat until well mixed, 2 or 3 minutes.
Bake in an 8 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost.
(I use white frosting.)

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Chop vegetables medium fine.
Chop or crush garlic.
Saute all in small amount of olive oil.
Chop wieners in 1/2-inch pieces. Add to vegetables and saute on medium heat until vegetables are tender and wieners are partially cooked.
Add tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Continue to cook on low heat to marry the flavor and the sauce has thickened.
Serve with or over mashed potatoes. Children love this.

title: hot mustard sweet sour sauce
directions: Cook over low heat until thick enough to dip.
Excellent with chicken.

title: diabetic pumpkin delight
directions: Place whole graham crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brush melted margarine over crackers.
Put cream cheese in bowl and beat with an electric mixer.
Mix spices into pumpkin and add to cream cheese.
Beat together.
Add Sugar Twin and milk and sprinkle in the dry pudding mix.
Mix into the pumpkin cream cheese mixture. Beat until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour and spread over crackers.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill overnight.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble. Reserve 2 tablespoons of the bacon drippings; saute onion in reserved bacon drippings until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
You can also cook this on top of stove on low heat until bubbly hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Put 1 teaspoon of apricot jelly on each piece.
Sprinkle entire package of dry onion soup over the 4 pieces of chicken.
Pour Russian dressing over all the pieces. Cook 1 hour at 350° or until chicken is cooked.

title: easy parmesan chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Flour and cook chicken until golden brown.
Place chicken in pan.
Add cheese slices on top of each breast.
Add sauce.
Shake Parmesan cheese to cover.
Bake until chicken is done and cheese is melted and browned, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet apples and carrots
directions: Boil carrots for about 5 to 8 minutes.
Put carrots and apples in baking dish; stir in just enough honey to cover the carrots and apples.
Add cinnamon to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, or until tender.

title: mush punch
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 2 containers.
Place in freezer.
One hour after placing in freezer, start stirring occasionally until slushy.

title: no bake summer cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight. Top with fresh fruit or cherry pie filling. Yield: 8 servings.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 1 1/2 cups of the flour, sugar, salt and the yeast.
Combine milk, water and butter in a saucepan. Heat until very warm (do not boil or let get real warm, it will "kill" the yeast).
The butter does not need to melt.
Gradually add warm mixture to dry ingredients and stir or beat for 2 minutes, scraping bowl as you work.
Add 1/2 cup more of the flour.
Stir. Gradually add more of the flour until you have a soft ball.
Knead and add more of the flour as necessary to make smooth and elastic. Place in a greased bowl, large enough for it to double in size. Set bowl in a pan of warm water and cover.
Let rise until double. Make sure bowl is warm.
When ready, shape into rolls and put in greased pan.
Let rise in warm place, covered and free from drafts. Bake at 425° about 12 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add sugar, basil, salt and pepper. Arrange one-half of tomatoes in 1-quart greased casserole.
Top with one-half bread cubes.
Repeat layer.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pita snack appetizers
directions: Slice pitas into approximately 1-inch strips and separate each strip into two pieces.
Discard edges of the two end pieces if desired.
Brush one side of each strip lightly with olive oil, seasoned with garlic powder.
Bake at 450° for 4 minutes on foil-lined cookie sheets.
Wipe off any extra oil from foil between batches to prevent overbrowning next batch.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Peel and slice potatoes. Mix melted oleo, flour, salt, milk and cheese. Put potatoes, mixture and small chunks of ham in casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: dirt cake
directions: In one bowl mix cookies, margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In separate bowl mix milk and both pudding mixes.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Layer cookie mixture and pudding mixture in a plastic flower pot (with no holes in bottom).
Reserve 1/2 cup cookies to sprinkle on top.

title: roast beaver
directions: Remove excess fat from beaver; rub with salt and pepper to taste.
Place in small roaster or roasting bag together with chunks of onion and green pepper; add 2 cans of beer.
Roast at 350° for 2 hours or until done.
Time will depend upon size of beaver.
Remove from bone to serve.

title: easy chicken stir-fry
directions: Pour oil into wok or skillet, coating bottom and sides; heat to medium high (325°) for 2 minutes.
Add chicken and almonds; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add vegetables; cover and cook 4 minutes stirring occasionally.
Combine soy sauce, pineapple juice and cornstarch; add to vegetables, and cook 2 minutes or until thickened.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Put cabbage in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Brown meat and onion.
Stir in rice and place on cabbage.
Add salt and pepper.
Combine soup and water; pour over all.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit soup
directions: Combine fruit and water.
Add approximately 3/4 cup red hots for color.
Heat.
Serve.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice. Cook broccoli and drain.
Add Cheez Whiz to hot broccoli; stir until melted, then add mushroom soup and pimentos. Mix well and bake in casserole dish at 350° until bubbly.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix in flour and cheese.
Mix with chopped broccoli.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Fold in beaten egg whites gently.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes in 325° oven.

title: barbecued oysters(quick and easy hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Put oysters and sauce in medium saucepan.
Simmer until edges curl and most of juice evaporates.	Add enough barbecue sauce to cover oysters and simmer for 5 minutes longer.
Serve hot or cold.

title: festive sweet potatoes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients except marshmallows.
Sprinkle over top of potato mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle marshmallows over.
Return to oven until marshmallows are brown and melted.

title: chocolate soda
directions: Combine club soda and chocolate syrup in a tall glass.
Add ice cream.
Fill glass with extra club soda.
Top with whipped topping and maraschino cherry.
Serve immediately.

title: john's favorite
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Brown and drain meat.
Cut cheese into small pieces and add to meat.
Add rice when done, then add tomatoes, taco mix and stir until cheese melts.
Serve with large Frito Scoops.

title: cookies for diabetics
directions: Mix together and drop by tablespoonfuls.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: gone-all-day stew
directions: Mix together soup, water and flour until smooth; combine with remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
When ready to serve, adjust seasoning, if desired. Serve over noodles or with crunchy French bread (to soak up the gravy).
Coleslaw is a nice winter accompaniment or serve fresh tomatoes on a bed of lettuce in summer.
Yields 8 servings.

title: mystery recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients except part of salt. Sprinkle both sides with salt.
Place skin side up in baking pan. Pour other mixture over chicken and bake 50 to 60 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: california summer egg salad
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Spoon mixture into half pita bread.

title: quickie oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and oleo in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter, stirring until peanut butter is dissolved.
Add oatmeal and nuts.
Stir well and drop on wax paper to cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: easy cake
directions: Bring fruit to boil in a saucepan; set aside to cool slightly.
Melt butter or margarine in the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Add the sugar, flour, baking powder and milk and mix together thoroughly.
Pour slightly cooled fruit over the batter; do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 30-40 minutes, or until cake tests done.

title: scalloped rhubarb
directions: In a medium bowl, toss bread cubes with margarine.
Add rhubarb, sugar and raisins; mix gently.
Turn mixture into a 1 1/2 quart casserole sprayed with nonstick coating.
Pour water over mixture.
(Amount of water depends on dryness of bread and moistness of rhubarb.)
Bake at 325°, covered, about 45 minutes or until slightly bubbly.
Serve with roast beef, pork, lamb, chicken or turkey.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and salt.
Mix water, cocoa and food coloring.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk and flour slowly and beat.
Add soda that has been dissolved in vinegar.

title: refrigerator white rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Heat milk.
Add shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour; beat well (2 to 3 minutes on medium speed).
Beat in yeast mixture and eggs.
Add remaining flour with wooden spoon; mix well.
Place in greased bowl; grease surface of dough.
Cover; store in refrigerator. Remove dough from refrigerator.
Roll out; cut with round cookie cutter or shape to your desire.

title: country corn bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine corn, soup, milk, celery, pimiento, seasoned salt, 1/4 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Crumble 3 slices bacon; stir into corn mixture.
Spoon corn mixture into 8-inch square baking dish. Bake, covered, at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Top with remaining bacon slices, cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken and mushrooms supreme
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on the chicken.
Place chicken in a covered casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Then place the sliced potatoes over the chicken.
Add can of golden mushroom soup.
Bake 10 minutes, covered.
Bake 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: inside out ravioli
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package, drain, saving liquid.
Set aside.
Brown ground chuck, onion and garlic in 1 Tbsp. oil.
Add enough water to spinach liquid to make 1 cup. Add spinach liquid, spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt and pepper to ground chuck mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes. Combine spinach, cooked macaroni, cheese, eggs and 1/4 cup oil. Spread spinach mixture in a 10x9x2 inch baking dish.
Spread meat mixture on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together, adding Doritos last. Mix well.

title: jean's apple cake
directions: Mix well, adding apples and nuts last.
Dough will be stiff. Bake 55 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan at 350°.

title: fork cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Combine other ingredients and mix with flour.
Add extra flour if too soft. Form into balls, press down on greased cookie sheet with fork. Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Combine ingredients in cooker.
