Cook slowly for 30 minutes, then add wieners and cook until they are heated.

title: peach-banana cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, pudding and pie filling mix and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Cool slightly.
Fold sliced fruit into filling.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking powder, ginger, salt and nutmeg.
Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Invert cake on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll up cake and towel jelly roll style, starting at short side.
Cool.

title: punch
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Mix fruit juices and water well.
Add ginger ale and then soda water.
Just before serving, add lime sherbet.
Yields 40 cups.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 10 x 14-inch pan.
Mix pecans and coconut; spread in bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla with oleo.
Spread over cake batter.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: monster chunk cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In medium bowl, whisk together flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl with electric mixer, cream the butter.
Beat in sugar until well combined.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, then add vanilla.
On low speed, blend in flour mixture, stirring last bit with wooden spoon.
Stir in chocolate chunks.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Soak beans in boiling water in large Dutch oven for 30 minutes; stir in salt.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 hours.
Saute diced onion and celery in melted margarine until tender.
Add sauteed vegetables and tomatoes to bean mixture, stirring well.
Simmer, uncovered, 1 hour or until beans are tender.
Serve hot.
Yields 11 servings (1 cup each). Calories:
Exchanges:
2 starch.

title: granny m's old fashion egg pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and egg yolks.
Beat and stir in the sweet milk and melted butter.
Pour all ingredients into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until done.
Then beat egg whites.
Add sugar and cream of tartar to make stiff.
Ice the egg pies and return to oven until brown.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Grease and flour a square cake pan, 6 x 8 x 2-inches.
In saucepan heat applesauce until hot throughout; remove from heat. Add oats and stir well.
Cover tightly and let stand 20 minutes. Mix flour, cinnamon, cloves, salt and baking soda together; set aside. In mixing bowl cream butter and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Gradually and gently beat in flour mixture.
Add applesauce-oats, stir well.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 55 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Rinse and dry shrimp.
Mix all ingredients together well and chill before serving.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a skillet, melt the shortening and add the ground meat.
Use a fork to break up the meat thoroughly, so it doesn't cook in chunks.
Stir in the onion and green pepper and saute until meat is browned.
Add the chili sauce, catsup and sugar.
Stir well until all ingredients are combined.
Cover and simmer gently over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.
Uncover and simmer until mixture is thick enough to spread.
Serve hot on buttered hamburger buns. Serves 6.

title: apple dip
directions: Beat all ingredients together with mixer.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons of milk for spreading consistency.
Serve as a dip for apple wedges.

title: punch for 150
directions: Mix sugar with 3 pints water and boil until dissolved. Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add juices.
This can be divided to make punch for 50 or 100.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and form into loaf; put into pan.
In can of remaining tomato sauce, add 2 heaping tablespoons of brown sugar and 1 teaspoon mustard.
Mix well.
Pour over loaf in pan.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: low-fat oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine flour, Egg Beaters, garlic powder, paprika, and milk to make a batter.
Dip chicken in mixture, then roll in corn flake crumbs.
Spray a casserole dish with cooking spray.
Place prepared chicken breasts in dish.
Bake 1 hour or until browned and done.

title: coconut date cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients with hands.
Make small balls and place 1 inch apart on lightly-greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool a few minutes and use spatula to remove and press balls while warm.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Microwave meat and onion for 5 to 6 minutes (Full power). Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheeses.
Microwave, covered, 15 to 17 minutes (Full).
Stir 2 to 3 times.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Microwave, uncovered, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes (Full). Superb!

title: grilled cheese stuffed hot dog
directions: With sharp knife, slice hot dogs lengthwise about 1/2 inch deep.
Cook, cut side down, on grill about 5 minutes.
Combine cheese, onions, relish, mustard and catsup.
Turn hot dogs.
Spoon cheese mixture down center of each hot dog.
Cook 5 minutes. Toast rolls on grill 2 to 3 minutes.
Place hot dogs in rolls. Makes 8.

title: easy sherried beef
directions: Stir all together.
Put in tightly covered casserole or Dutch oven.
Bake
about	4
hours
at
Baking longer at low temperature makes it even better.
Serve on wild rice.

title: uncle mac's cobbler
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk and mix well.
Melt oleo in 13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 3/4-inch casserole.
Pour flour mixture over melted oleo in casserole dish.
Pile on fruit and juice.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: jewish kugel
directions: Mix cheese, sour cream, eggs, raisins, sugar, vanilla and apples.
Add cooked noodles; mix well.
Pour batter into one large or two 13 x 9-inch pans.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, shortening, soda and salt.
Add eggs.
Add mincemeat.
Gradually add flour and nuts.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400°
for 12 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Soak pickles in powdered alum and water for 2 to 3 hours. Boil remaining ingredients (except grape leaves) for 5 minutes. Pour over pickles.
Place 1 grape leaf over pickles.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out dough in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Place cooked and drained sausage over raw dough, then top with other ingredients.
Pour eggs over top; bake until done (about 1 hour).

title: marjo's bread
directions: *For whole
wheat
bread, use 3 cups white flour plus 2 cups whole wheat flour.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs into halves lengthwise and carefully remove yolks. Mash yolks with mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Stuff eggs with the yolk mixture.
Garnish with paprika.

title: roast beef cuban style
directions: Marinate the beef with garlic, sour orange, salt and pepper for 3 hours.
With a knife, open six holes in the beef and put the ham inside, adding the onion and the green pepper.
Put in pot the oil and the beef, cook it on both sides.
Add garlic and wine and water and cook slowly.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Pour water over raisins just to cover.
Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes.
While raisins are cooking, measure sugar, cornstarch and salt in small bowl.
Drain raisins.
Keep the juice and add Pet milk and regular milk (enough to make 3 cups).
Add milk mixture to dry ingredients to raisins.
Stir until smooth, then cook on medium heat to a soft boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir.
Let cool to room temperature.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Make strips for the top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: beef chow mein
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Measure fat into pan; brown onion. Add celery, Chinese vegetables, hot water, salt and soy sauce. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine cornstarch with cold water; add to mixture.
Cook until thickened, stirring continuously.
Serve 3/4 cup over 1/2 cup rice per serving.
Yield: 4 servings. Carbohydrate 39 g, protein 18 g, fat 12 g, calories 336.
One serving = 2 meat medium fat exchange, 2 bread starch exchange, 1 fruit exchange.

title: tropicana cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oil well.
Add oranges and mix.
Bake in two 9-inch layer pans or 11 x 14-inch pan, according to package directions.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients together in baking bowl.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In bowl, combine 2 tablespoons sugar with flour, baking powder and salt; then cut in butter.
Combine egg and milk and mix, stirring just until moist.
Pit, peel and slice peaches; combine in a saucepan with remaining sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Cook medium heat until syrup is clear, thick and boiling 5 to 7 minutes.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish and drop dough in heaping tablespoons.
Makes 6 portions.
Bake at 400° until golden, about 20 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix together, beating very well.
Bake at 350° until done (about 30 or 35 minutes).
Makes 3 or 4 layers.

title: christmas treats
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips; stir together.
In large bowl, mix marshmallows with chocolate.
Sprinkle coconut on waxed paper.
Spoon marshmallow mix onto it.
Roll to make logs.
Place in freezer.
Before serving, slice in sections about 1-inch thick.

title: spud cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and potato flakes.
Add to the shortening mixture.
Mix well.
Add nuts and mix.
Batter will be stiff.
Let set 30 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and serve with your favorite raw vegetables.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently, for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter; mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well blended.
Press mixture into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: french apple pie
directions: Lay out shell.
Arrange apples in shell.
Sprinkle lemon juice. Sprinkle nutmeg and cinnamon.
Spread sugar.
Spread raisins.
Mix brown sugar and flour and spread over all.
Add pecans.
Add butter.
Add water.
Put on top crust.
Brush lightly with milk. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm with Hard Sauce (optional).

title: strawberry pie
directions: Fill crust with strawberries and make filling with remaining ingredients.
Combine water, sugar and cornstarch in saucepan. Bring to a boil and add gelatin.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool and pour over strawberries.
Chill for 3 hours.
Top with whipped topping and garnish with remaining strawberries.

title: crazy self-filling cupcakes
directions: Mix ingredients together and beat well.
Fill paper baking cups 2/3 full.

title: swiss cheese chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in a 4 x 8-inch baking dish or pan.
Lay Swiss cheese on top of chicken.
Mix soup and milk together; pour over chicken and cheese.
Put thick layer of stuffing over chicken, cheese and soup.
Cover with Reynolds Wrap; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Chill (if necessary) and roll into balls (smaller than walnuts).
Roll in a mixture of 2 teaspoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, until light brown, but soft.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: maine blueberry cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add vanilla and eggs, one at a time and beat.
Add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Fold in blueberries. Place in large tube pan, greased and floured.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: all bean casserole
directions: Put onions, brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and garlic powder in a crock-pot and heat until sugar melts.
Add beans and bacon. Cover and cook on high for 2 1/2 hours, then reduce heat to low or simmer for 3 hours more.

title: pear honey or pear butter
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in heavy pan, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes.
Put through a food mill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, drain, put in large mixing bowl.
Add cream of mushroom and cream of chicken.
Add stick of melted margarine and the onion, diced in small pieces; mix well, then add crackers and cheese.
Mix together, put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with cheese and crackers.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: six weeks bran muffins
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Store in the refrigerator.
Will keep up to 6 weeks.
Just use as needed.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes.
Cover slices with flour, salt and pepper.
Fry in pan with butter flavored Crisco until golden brown.

title: kulma(norwegian potato balls, or something like them)
directions: Cook ham hock for 2 hours in a large pot of water.
Remove the ham hock from the water.
Spoon or form by hand dumplings (say about the size of a snowball).
Drop the "dumplings" in the water (or broth by now).
Cover; cook for 45 minutes.
Remove "dumplings" from the water; serve on a platter with the ham.
Just slice open the "dumpling" as you would a baked potato and add butter.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles and the frozen spinach according to package directions.
Drain; press water out of spinach and set aside.

title: walnut caramels
directions: Butter sides of heavy 5-quart Dutch oven.
In it, melt butter. Add brown sugar and dash of salt.
Stir until thoroughly combined.
Stir in light corn syrup; mix well.
Gradually add cream, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir over medium heat to firm-ball stage (245°), about 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from heat. Place nuts in bottom of buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour syrup over nuts.
Cool; cut in squares.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: rum slush
directions: Mix in ice cream pail.
Add 2 drops of green food coloring and freeze.

title: chocolate-pecan chess pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Combine eggs, milk and vanilla; stir into sugar mixture.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Wash and grease potatoes.
Bake and slice lengthwise.
Scoop out potatoes while hot and mash with margarine.
Add sour cream. Saute onions with a little margarine and add to potato mix.
Add part of the grated cheese to the potatoes.
Replace in the potato jacket.
Reheat just before serving, garnishing the tops with grated cheese, melting slightly.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir well.
Heat an oblong pan.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Heat skillet over medium-high heat.
Add beef and cook, stirring with a fork, until meat is broken up and has lost its red color.
Stir
in
onion
soup mix, tomato sauce and water. Reduce heat
and
simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles, drain well and let stand in cool water for easier separating.
Heat oven to 400°.
In a 2-quart oblong baking dish, alternate layers of noodles, meat sauce
and
cheese,
ending in cheese.
Bake 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken and pineapple
directions: Dredge chicken pieces in flour, coating well.
Brown in hot oil over medium heat.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: baked beans and sausage
directions: *You can replace dried onion with regular onion.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Dredge fruit in flour.
Add other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet lined with foil. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 275°.
Store in airtight can about 5 days before serving.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips with peanut butter. Spread half in bottom of buttered 13 x 9-inch pan and cool.
Barely boil margarine, pudding mix and milk.
Add powdered sugar and maple flavoring.
Spread onto cooled chocolate layer.
Cool.
Add peanuts to second half of chocolate mixture and spread onto cooled pudding mixture.
Cool.
These can be frozen.

title: child raising
directions: Mix all the ingredients and a pound of persistence, 1 c.
of love and whip until right consistency.
This recipe is recommended by the Creator of Mankind.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix and Jell-O, dry.
Add the oil, milk, eggs, strawberries, nuts and coconut.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chinese beef
directions: Fry first 6 ingredients until brown.
Add beef bouillon and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook 10 minutes over low flame.
Add pea pods; cook 5 minutes.
Add mixture of cornstarch, soy sauce and 1/4 cup water.
After thick and shiny, add tomatoes.
Serve with Fried Rice.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini patties
directions: After grating the zucchini, squeeze out as much liquid as possible with hands. Combine zucchini, onion, parsley, cheese and 1 cup bread crumbs with salt, pepper and eggs. Shape into patties and brush with melted butter. Bake in a 350 degree oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown. You can fry these patties in a skillet with butter.

title: fruit cocktail butter sauce cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch floured pan. Sprinkle with 3/4 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon into pie crust. Top with second crust and flute.
Cut slits in several places. Bake at 435° for 40 to 50 minutes, until apples are tender and crust is golden brown.

title: beef stew
directions: Saute beef and onion in 2 tablespoons Wesson oil.
Add 3 cups water and other ingredients.
Grate 1 potato into the mixture. This thickens the mixture.
Cook slowly until thick.

title: acorn squash rustica
directions: Carefully cut squash in half horizontally (not through stem end). Remove seeds and stringy portions.
Using 1 tsp. butter, rub the cut surfaces of squash.
Place cut-side-up in shallow baking pan with 1/2 inch water.
In small skillet melt 2 tsp. butter. Saute onions and celery until tender.
In medium bowl combine sauteed vegetables, prepared stuffing, turkey and orange pieces. Spoon into squash halves.

Cover squash loosely with foil. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes. Remove foil, bake 15 minutes longer or until squash is tender and stuffing is lightly browned. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 2 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost frozen hash browns.
Butter bottom of a large baking dish.
Add margarine to hash browns.
Mix together grated cheese, chicken soup, salt, green onions, sour cream and pepper.
Pour over potatoes and mix well.
Put in dish.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese on top and sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix together and bake in greased angel food cake pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dunking platter oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, oats, Grape Nut flakes, flour, baking powder and baking soda. Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes.

title: microwave chocolate cake
directions: Grease microwave pan.
Cook on 70% power for 12 to 18 minutes, depends on microwave.
Let sit 5 to 10 minutes and then invert.
The chocolate chips will act as frosting.
Very good.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Put broccoli in bowl.
Pour rice over broccoli. Melt remaining ingredients, except the dried onions, in a medium saucepan.
Stir in 3/4 cup dried onions and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Put remaining onions on top for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add slightly beaten egg and make crumbs.
Cover bottom of buttered Pyrex casserole with thinly sliced apples and spread with crumb mixture.
Melt butter and sprinkle over it.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Peaches, cherries or any fruit can be substituted.
Serves 6.

title: "red lobster" cheese biscuits
directions: Mix flour, cayenne pepper and mustard in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening and fold in cheese.
Add enough milk to make a batter stiff enough to drop.
Drop biscuits on a greased cookie sheet. Brush tops with melted butter and sprinkle with garlic powder or garlic salt.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon and reserve fat.
Add onions to fat and saute.
Add water and potatoes; boil slowly 20 minutes.
Add milk and corn. Simmer 15 minutes more.
Stir in pepper, salt and Tabasco.	Crumble bacon and add with sour cream.
Simmer (do not boil) 5 minutes more.
Garnish with parsley or paprika.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: unbaked banana pudding
directions: Layer wafers and bananas.
Mix all other ingredients together. Hold back a 1/2 cup of Cool Whip to spread on top.
Pour the mixture over the bananas and wafers.
Spread the 1/2 cup of Cool Whip on top.

title: heath bar torte
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar slowly, beat in egg yolks one at a time.
Add vanilla and set aside.
Whip cream and add to butter mixture.
Break half of angel food cake into 9 x 13-inch pan; top with cream mixture.
Sprinkle with 3 Heath bars, repeat with remaining cake, cream and candy.
Refrigerate.

title: ice cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolk and vanilla.
Beat well. Add flour.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
If desired, decorate with nuts or candy.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and fluff, beat with mixer until light and fluffy.
Serve with a platter of assorted fruit wedges, slices, etc.

title: rice pudding
directions: In large saucepan, bring the milk to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Return to heat and allow milk to reach a lively simmer.
Add the rice and sugar.
Stir well to prevent the rice from sticking.
Cook until the rice is done, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk; let stand.
Combine pudding and cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Put 1/2 cookie crumbs in pan; press.
Put pudding mixture next.
Chill 4 hours.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Add brown sugar to melted butter and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and blend.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Mix in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in 2 greased 8-inch square pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: dirt and worms
directions: Mix the instant pudding and milk together.
Mix the cream cheese together with pudding mixture until well blended.
Fold Cool Whip into the pudding and cream cheese mixture; mix well. Divide crushed Oreo cookies in half.
Fold into mixture 1/2 of the cookie crumbs.
Mix in the gummy worms.
Place mixture into a clean, large flowerpot.
Add the rest of cookie crumbs on top. Refrigerate.
Before serving, decorate with a few silk flowers or holiday theme.

title: kids' eggnog
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat with beater until creamy.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar and vanilla well.
Sift flour into bowl; add potatoes and Crisco; gradually add the milk.
Handle the dough as little as possible.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut; place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400 degrees for about 20 minutes.
They should be lightly browned.
Makes 25 biscuits with 2 - 1/2 inch cutter (about the size of a vienna sausage can). These can be eaten at any meal.

title: tomato-sour cream dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with chips or fresh vegetables.

title: giant meatball sub
directions: In a large bowl, combine the eggs, milk, onion, garlic, bread crumbs, salt and Italian seasoning. Crumble sausage and beef over mixture; mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until browned.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water; let cool.
Add pineapple (drained).
Use pineapple juice to beat with cream cheese.
Add this mixture and Cool Whip to jello and refrigerate.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine dry ingredients and mix with butter until small crumbs form.
Add raisins and buttermilk.
Stir until moistened.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Place sugar, milk, margarine, vanilla and cocoa in a large pot.
Bring these ingredients to a full boil.
Boil for 1 minute. Then quickly add peanut butter and oats.
Stir and spoon out by tablespoons onto cookie sheet to cool.

title: pumpkin swirl cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and butter; press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla; mix at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs and mix well. Reserve one cup cheese mixture; add pumpkin and remaining sugar and spices to remaining cheese.
Mix well.
Layer half of pumpkin and half cheese mixture over crust.
Repeat layers.
Cut through layers with knife several times to make a marble effect. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim.
Cool before removing cake.
Chill.

title: buckeyes
directions: Soften butter.
Mix ingredients together with mixer or by hand, except chocolate chips and wax.
Roll into balls.
Cut paraffin wax into thin shavings prior to melting chocolate.
Melt chocolate chips and wax together; dip balls into melted chocolate.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Line pie plate with pastry.
Build up edges. Brush bottom with melted shortening and dust with a little flour to prevent custard from soaking in. Scald and cool milk.
Mix together sugar, flour and salt.
Add beaten eggs.
Next, add milk and flavoring. Stir in 3/4 cup coconut.

Turn into pie plate and bake at 450° for 15 minutes until pastry begins to brown. Sprinkle over top of custard the remaining 1/4 cup coconut. Reduce heat to 325° and return to oven and bake until custard is set, 30 minutes.

title: quick summer italian salad
directions: Clean mushrooms with damp paper towels.
Remove stems and reserve for other uses.
Combine mushroom caps and remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and chill.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg; add shortening, eggs and orange peel and juice.
Mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by tablespoons of dough on greased cookie sheet (approximately 2-inches apart).
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: oriental beef and broccoli
directions: Slice steak at an angle, 1/4-inch thick.
Slice about 2-inches long.
Combine sherry, cornstarch, soy sauce, ginger and sugar in a bowl.
Add beef slices, mix well and set aside.
Cut broccoli flowerets into bite-size pieces.
Peel stalks and slice diagonally into small pieces.
Dry with paper towel and sprinkle with salt. Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok.
Add broccoli and cook quickly while stirring, until bright and crisp.
Remove from pan and keep warm. Add remaining oil to pan and heat.
Stir in beef mixture, water chestnuts and scallions.
Cook quickly until beef is cooked to desired degree of doneness (about 2 minutes).
Add broccoli and serve with rice.

title: lo-fat chicken
directions: Chop onion, pepper and mushrooms.
Saute in skillet that has been sprayed with Pam.
Can add a little bit of water.
Put in heavy pan; add tomatoes and skinned chicken pieces.
Cover and cook on low heat 1 to 1 1/2 hours until chicken is tender.
Can serve over rice.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Pour in remaining ingredients.
Mix all together in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Fry meat and onion; drain.
Put all in Dutch oven; simmer until squash is well done (tender).
(Mixture is like Sloppy Joes when done.)

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix well; pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Preheat oven to 400°, about 5 minutes.
After putting pies in oven, reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Melt butter; set aside.
Mix powdered sugar, salt and cocoa. Add enough milk to make of spreading consistency.
Then add melted butter and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.

title: moist cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat all ingredients for 2 minutes. Batter will be thin.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use 8 or 9-inch round or square cake pans.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sour cream, egg, corns and muffin mix. Put into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: original maxson manor orange rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Cream together sugar and Crisco. Add beaten eggs, then remaining 2 cups warm water. Add salt and dissolved yeast.
Stir in flour, 2 cups at a time. Dough should not be too sticky. Add orange peel. Cover and let rise until double. Punch dough and knead a short time.
Shape into round balls to half fill a muffin pan.
Let rise. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
May be glazed with glaze made with powdered sugar and orange juice.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine milk and sugar in saucepan.
Heat until boiling.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Combine preceding ingredients and set aside.
Drop 8 to 10 cabbage leaves in hot water to wilt.
Place equal portions of meat mixture in center of each cabbage leaf.
Fold over and fasten with toothpicks.
Place cabbage rolls in a deep baking dish.
Pour 1 (10 3/4 ounce) can of tomato sauce and equal amount of water over cabbage rolls and simmer approximately 1 1/2 hours.
This can also be baked, covered, in the oven at 375°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix together and add dressing.

title: jello pie
directions: Put milk in freezing compartment of refrigerator to chill until ice flakes begin to form.
Mix pineapple juice, flavored gelatin and sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring while it heats. Cool.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and combine with other ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 300° to 350° until bubbly (30 to 45 minutes).
Can be baked in microwave.

title: white lasagna
directions: Mix together the mushroom soup, soup mix and spinach.
Boil noodles.
Layer sauce mixture, cheeses and noodles together.
Add milk to sauce if too thick or if you need to make more sauce.

title: cranberry relish salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in sugar, mixing well. Add all other ingredients, mixing well. Pour into serving dish and refrigerate 4 hours to overnight. Serve and enjoy.

title: vegetable sandwiches 1
directions: Combine cabbage, bell pepper, cucumber, carrots and onion, blending well.
In a saucepan, soften gelatin in water.
Add vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt, pepper and paprika. Cook over medium heat until gelatin dissolves, stirring constantly.
Blend into vegetables.
Refrigerate to let flavors meld at least 1 day, preferably 2.
Add mayonnaise just before serving.
Makes about 10 sandwiches or 30 finger sandwiches.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese with milk to dipping consistency.
Add shrimp, horseradish and onion.
Serve with potato chips or crackers.

title: chicken, rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken and rice.
Place in large casserole dish.
Add uncooked frozen broccoli.
Pour cheese soup into a saucepan and add 1 to 2 cups water (you still need it thick).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, and then 15 minutes uncovered.
Top with grated cheese and sprinkle with paprika.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Pour into baking dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: classic walnut pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine eggs, sugar, flour, corn syrup, butter and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Arrange walnuts on top.
Bake in lower third of oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake an additional 35 to 45 minutes or until center appears set.
Cool completely.
Makes 8 servings.
Prep.
Time:
10 minutes.
Bake time:
50 to 60 minutes.

title: green beans in herb sauce
directions: Saute onion, celery and parsley flakes in margarine in medium saucepan until onion is golden.
Mix the garlic salt, salt, pepper and cornstarch.
Slowly stir in 1 cup water to form a smooth paste.
Add mixture and green beans to onions.
Cover; gently cook for 10 minutes, or until beans are tender-crisp and sauce has thickened slightly.
Yields 4 servings.

title: salisbury steak with mushroom-onion gravy
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons soup mix and 1/4 cup water in large bowl. Add beef and parsley and mix until blended.
Shape into 4 oval patties, about 5 inches long and 2/3 inch thick. Coat patties with 1 1/2 tablespoon flour.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium. heat.
Add patties and cook about 10 minutes, turning once, until crusty and no longer pink in the middle.
Remove to a plate and keep warm.
Add onion, mushrooms and 1/4 cup water to the drippings in skillet.
Deglaze pan with wooden spoon.
Turn heat to medium-low, cover and cook, stirring occasionally until onion and mushrooms are soft. Mix remaining soup mix, 1 1/2 cup water and 2 1/2 tablespoons flour in a small bowl.
Stir into mushroom mixture, add bouillon cube and bring to a boil.
Cook, stirring often, until thickened.
Return patties to skillet and turn to coat with gravy. Remove to plates and serve with remaining gravy.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt, sugar, nutmeg and vanilla.
Dip bread slices into mixture and place on griddle or in a frying pan. Lightly toast one side, then turn it over and toast other side.

title: surprise corn bread sticks
directions: Combine sugar, honey and butter in a small saucepan, stirring occasionally, over low heat until it boils and sugar is dissolved. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon nuts into each of 12 average-sized corn stick forms.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons of the hot syrup over the nuts.
Prepare corn bread mix, according to package directions. Pour into corn stick forms.
Bake 25 minutes at 450° until lightly browned.
Immediately invert onto serving platter and serve hot.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray pizza pan with nonstick spray.
Put cookie dough into pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool and mix cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread mixture on cookie. Cover with well drained pineapple.
Arrange sliced bananas on top of pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Place sliced strawberries on top, then coconut and pecans.
Keep refrigerated.
May substitute fruits to suite your taste.

title: peas and meatball dinner
directions: Mix egg and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over bread crumbs.
Add salt, pepper, mustard, celery, salt, nutmeg, onion and ground beef.
Mix well and shape into balls.
Roll in flour.
Brown slowly.
Remove and add soup and 3/4 cup milk.
Cook until smooth.
Add peas.

title: mystery salad
directions: Soak plain gelatin in cold water.
Boil the pineapple and juice; add gelatin, cottage cheese and black walnut meats.
Pour into large tray and chill in refrigerator.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Add tomato juice, corn, pork and beans and chile.
Mix and simmer about 2 or 3 hours.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Remove frosting from center of cookies.
Crush cookies with rolling pin.
Put cookie crumbs in medium bowl, reserving 1 cup crumbs for topping.
Add melted butter to cookie crumbs and mix well.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes; cool.

title: i can't believe it's a cookie
directions: Beat egg and sugar until they are light and fluffy. Fold in peanut butter. Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and press chocolate star into each cookie. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw dough.
Spread on cookie sheet like pizza crust.
Mix next 7 ingredients and spread on dough like butter.
Cover with pepperoni, Mozzarella, ham and mushrooms if you desire.
Roll like jelly roll from long end.
Place seam down and brush with egg white.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Slice and serve with bowl of heated pizza sauce for dipping.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Boil sugar, water, vanilla and cornstarch until thick.
Add remaining ingredients, except rhubarb, and crumble 3/4 in the bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add rhubarb and cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken taco bake
directions: Blend enchilada sauce and soup. Stir in chicken or turkey and onions.
Grease a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with half of the corn chips.
Pour chicken mixture over. Sprinkle with cheese, then remaining corn chips.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until heated through.

title: scrumptious black walnut pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk; beat well.
Add flavoring.

title: quick soup
directions: Cook all 45 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Meanwhile, cook separately about 1/2 bag narrow noodles.
Add to the pot of vegetables. Cook a few minutes longer.
Delicious.

title: candy jello delights
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft.
Add the jello; then mix together.
Add sugar and coconut.
Let set until firm or chill for an hour.
Take small amounts and mold into tiny egg-shaped pieces. Place on waxed paper until set.
These make delicious easy Easter eggs.
Makes about 6 dozen.
